01:30.750 --> 01:33.125
- Kara, I know you don t
want to be here.

01:33.125 --> 01:35.750
So why don t we finish this,

01:35.750 --> 01:37.500
here and now,

01:37.500 --> 01:39.125
so you can both disconnect

01:39.125 --> 01:42.583
and be happy?

01:42.583 --> 01:44.166
- Go on.

01:44.166 --> 01:46.834
- What about July
through December for Kara?

01:46.834 --> 01:49.333
She ll get summer months
and the Fourth of July.

01:49.333 --> 01:52.083
Then Mr. Tavares will have
Memorial Day and June.

01:54.583 --> 01:56.125
- That s fine.
- Okay.

01:56.125 --> 01:59.083
- Fantastic. Okay?
Moving on.

02:02.542 --> 02:04.917
- The Tavares are moving forward
with the divorce.

02:04.917 --> 02:06.166
I can t believe it.

02:06.166 --> 02:08.041
You re, like,
the divorce whisperer.

02:08.041 --> 02:09.834
- Well, I just hope
that it catches

02:09.834 --> 02:10.875
the attention of the partners.

02:10.875 --> 02:13.000
- How could it not?

02:13.000 --> 02:14.875
So did Teddy call you?

02:14.875 --> 02:18.083
- Yeah, we are, uh,
dining tonight, actually.

02:18.083 --> 02:19.542
I ve got to get
the list ready.

02:19.542 --> 02:20.750
- Oh, please don t bring
the list.

02:20.750 --> 02:22.834
- Hey, Kelsey, Stacee.

02:22.834 --> 02:25.166
Great job
on the Tavares account.

02:25.166 --> 02:28.583
- Will you tell Jason?
- He already did.

02:28.583 --> 02:31.041
You did great.
- Thank you, Jason.

02:31.041 --> 02:33.083
- Would you like to join Mitch
in the conference room?

02:33.083 --> 02:34.250
- The Ballentines
have it booked.

02:34.250 --> 02:36.375
- Yes, they do.
- You want me

02:36.375 --> 02:38.375
on the Ballentine account?
With Mitch?

02:38.375 --> 02:40.250
- I think you re ready.
Do you?

02:40.250 --> 02:42.750
- Absolutely.
- All right, go and do it, then.

02:50.208 --> 02:53.125
- Looks like it was just
a spider bite.

02:53.125 --> 02:54.750
Just give him these
as prescribed,

02:54.750 --> 02:57.125
and he should be back to normal
in a day or two.

02:57.125 --> 02:59.041
- Thank you so much,
Dr. Curry.

02:59.041 --> 03:00.792
You have no idea
the difference

03:00.792 --> 03:03.542
this little dog s made
in my dad s life.

03:03.542 --> 03:05.625
After my mother passed away,
he was so heartbroken,

03:05.625 --> 03:07.417
he wouldn t even
leave the house.

03:07.417 --> 03:09.291
- I really didn t do anything.

03:09.291 --> 03:12.583
Most people just need
companionship and loyalty.

03:12.583 --> 03:13.834
Pets provide that, Miss Reed.

03:13.834 --> 03:16.041
- Please, call me Jessica.

03:16.041 --> 03:17.417
Thank you.

03:17.417 --> 03:18.625
- Just doing my job.

03:21.083 --> 03:22.500
- Let s move on to vehicles,
shall we?

03:22.500 --> 03:24.333
- Well, I obviously
get the Porsche.

03:24.333 --> 03:26.417
- And why would you
get the Porsche?

03:26.417 --> 03:28.375
- If you would like
to make this difficult,

03:28.375 --> 03:30.834
just give me the jet,
and we ll call it a day.

03:30.834 --> 03:33.291
Fine.

03:33.291 --> 03:35.375
You can have the Porsche.

03:35.375 --> 03:36.917
- Now it s just a matter
of the dog.

03:36.917 --> 03:38.458
- She s mine.
- No, she s mine.

03:38.458 --> 03:41.041
- She s mine.
- So you both want the dog?

03:41.041 --> 03:43.125
- Can you excuse us a second?

03:43.125 --> 03:45.542
Oh, and take the dog.
I don t want her to hear this.

03:45.542 --> 03:46.542
- Take the dog.

03:49.542 --> 03:54.625
♪ ♪

03:54.625 --> 03:56.000
- Uh, wait a second.

03:56.000 --> 03:58.959
Why don t you stay?
I might need a witness.

04:04.667 --> 04:06.000
- You want me to do what?

04:06.000 --> 04:08.667
- It s the only way
to close out this divorce.

04:08.667 --> 04:10.709
- I just didn t think
that my contribution

04:10.709 --> 04:13.417
would be so... hairy.

04:13.417 --> 04:16.083
- Well, it s just temporary.

04:16.083 --> 04:18.500
You do want to be partner of
this firm someday, don t you?

04:18.500 --> 04:21.583
- Of course.
I will take care of the dog.

04:21.583 --> 04:23.500
Great.

04:26.000 --> 04:27.250
- Uh, does it have a name?

04:27.250 --> 04:28.208
- Daisy.

04:29.500 --> 04:30.542
- Daisy.

04:30.542 --> 04:35.625
♪ ♪

04:35.625 --> 04:38.417
Hey, Mom.
I could stay.

04:38.417 --> 04:41.792
I mean, I ve yet to even meet
this Teddy guy,

04:41.792 --> 04:43.875
and it could be beneficial

04:43.875 --> 04:47.250
gauging his reaction
to rescheduling the date.

04:47.250 --> 04:49.041
If he flips out,
he could be a lunatic.

04:49.041 --> 04:51.041
- That s what the date s for.

04:52.875 --> 04:54.875
Will she be all right?

04:54.875 --> 04:56.542
- Oh, honey, I had
six dogs growing up.

04:56.542 --> 04:58.041
I think I m okay
with this one.

04:58.041 --> 04:59.375
How long is this for again?

04:59.375 --> 05:01.542
- Two months.
- Two months?

05:01.542 --> 05:02.875
You need a dog walker.

05:02.875 --> 05:04.375
- Yeah...

05:04.375 --> 05:06.166
- Fine. I ll do it.

05:06.166 --> 05:07.375
- What are you doing?

05:07.375 --> 05:08.792
- Lovishness.

05:08.792 --> 05:10.333
It s a social app for singles.

05:10.333 --> 05:12.834
Ooh, this guy
is a retired firefighter.

05:12.834 --> 05:14.250
We ve been chatting.

05:14.250 --> 05:16.250
- Okay, where s my list?

05:16.250 --> 05:19.083
- No, come on.
You re taking the list?

05:19.083 --> 05:21.667
- I always take the list.

05:23.417 --> 05:24.875
- Bye.

05:24.875 --> 05:28.083
- Good-bye. Have fun.

05:28.083 --> 05:29.583
Go easy on him.

05:35.208 --> 05:37.583
- Hey, how s the budget looking?

05:37.583 --> 05:39.333
- Not too good.

05:39.333 --> 05:41.083
Looks like we ll have to ask
for an increased grant

05:41.083 --> 05:43.667
of 8 % just to break even.

05:43.667 --> 05:46.333
- There s no way the board
is gonna allow that.

05:46.333 --> 05:48.583
Last year, the change
was a 3 % decrease.

05:50.667 --> 05:51.834
What about raising the fees

05:51.834 --> 05:53.417
and general costs
that we charge people?

05:53.417 --> 05:54.583
- Some of our patients
have owners

05:54.583 --> 05:56.458
who can barely afford
the cost as it is.

05:56.458 --> 05:57.959
- Sometimes you re fine
if they don t even pay at all.

05:57.959 --> 05:59.959
- I m gonna rework
the budget proposal,

05:59.959 --> 06:01.417
and if I really stress

06:01.417 --> 06:03.792
all the good
that these animals do,

06:03.792 --> 06:05.041
the board ll have to increase
the grant.

06:05.041 --> 06:07.542
- And if they don t?

06:07.542 --> 06:10.500
That grant is our largest
source of income.

06:10.500 --> 06:12.000
- I m sure they ll approve it.

06:12.000 --> 06:14.709
They have to.

06:14.709 --> 06:15.834
- All right.

06:21.333 --> 06:24.500
- So how do you know Stacee?

06:24.500 --> 06:28.166
- Oh, uh, we met
at a charity run last year.

06:28.166 --> 06:30.458
- Oh, she does, like,
100 of those a year.

06:30.458 --> 06:33.667
- Well, uh, she told me
to give her my card

06:33.667 --> 06:36.208
if I wanted to meet
the girl of my dreams.

06:36.208 --> 06:37.834
- Stacee said what?

06:37.834 --> 06:39.917
- I gave her my card
cause it sounded intriguing.

06:39.917 --> 06:43.166
Hmm.

06:43.166 --> 06:46.709
So your eating habits
are normal, good.

06:46.709 --> 06:49.291
And, uh, what was your favorite
baseball team?

06:49.291 --> 06:50.959
- Did you just say
my eating is normal?

06:50.959 --> 06:54.125
- And are you more of an Elvis
or Beatles fan?

06:54.125 --> 06:56.208
- Is this a test?
- No!

06:56.208 --> 06:58.792
- It sounds like you re reading
from a list.

06:58.792 --> 07:02.625
Are you reading from a list?

07:02.625 --> 07:03.625
That s--

07:03.625 --> 07:05.709
- I m trying
to get a sense

07:05.709 --> 07:08.166
of our compatibility.

07:08.166 --> 07:10.458
- Well, that s very, uh...

07:10.458 --> 07:11.458
clinical.

07:11.458 --> 07:12.667
- No. No.

07:12.667 --> 07:14.333
I mean, you don t have to fit
every category.

07:18.542 --> 07:20.333
- What kind of lawyer
did you say you were again?

07:20.333 --> 07:22.500
- I specialize
in divorce mediation.

07:26.750 --> 07:28.250
- Excuse me?

07:28.250 --> 07:30.166
Yeah, can we get
the check, please?

07:30.166 --> 07:31.333
- Of course.

07:38.709 --> 07:45.375
♪ ♪

07:51.417 --> 07:53.166
- Hey.

07:53.166 --> 07:55.333
Still grading papers?

07:55.333 --> 07:56.959
- Yes, I am.

07:59.875 --> 08:01.333
You had a late one?

08:01.333 --> 08:02.959
- Yeah, I know.

08:02.959 --> 08:05.333
I m sorry.

08:05.333 --> 08:07.333
- Well, there s some chicken
in the fridge.

08:07.333 --> 08:10.500
- Being a first-year partner
is a crazy workload.

08:10.500 --> 08:12.375
There s so many clients,
so many people under me,

08:12.375 --> 08:15.583
and then there s
dealing with Jason.

08:15.583 --> 08:17.125
I mean, that guy is a bit--

08:17.125 --> 08:18.166
- A bit strange?

08:18.166 --> 08:19.625
- He thinks outside the box.

08:22.333 --> 08:25.125
- How s the world s best
history teacher doing?

08:25.125 --> 08:26.959
- Well, I might have to take

08:26.959 --> 08:28.834
a leave of absence
in the near future.

08:28.834 --> 08:30.959
- Why?

08:30.959 --> 08:32.500
- I m pregnant.

08:32.500 --> 08:34.750
- That s fantastic.

08:34.750 --> 08:36.625
Yeah.

08:36.625 --> 08:38.542
- Okay, so tell me, tell me,
tell me, tell me, tell me.

08:38.542 --> 08:41.000
- Well, technically, it s not
completely official yet.

08:41.000 --> 08:43.207
The pregnancy test was positive,

08:43.207 --> 08:45.959
but I made an appointment
with my doctor to make sure.

08:48.959 --> 08:55.875
♪ ♪

08:58.041 --> 09:00.125
- So how d it go?

09:00.125 --> 09:03.458
- Mm-mm.

09:03.458 --> 09:06.208
Hey, Daisy.

09:06.208 --> 09:07.709
Sit.

09:07.709 --> 09:09.208
- You have to give her
something.

09:09.208 --> 09:10.625
Here, I brought her
these treats.

09:10.625 --> 09:12.041
She loves em.
- It s a sit.

09:12.041 --> 09:13.959
She doesn t need a treat.

09:13.959 --> 09:15.625
- If she s gonna do something,
she needs to get something.

09:15.625 --> 09:17.458
She knows that.

09:17.458 --> 09:19.125
- Hey, Daisy.

09:19.125 --> 09:20.125
Sit.

09:20.125 --> 09:21.625
- See?

09:21.625 --> 09:23.709
- Great, so she s gonna
get fat

09:23.709 --> 09:25.208
learning how to sit.

09:25.208 --> 09:27.000
- She can read
your attitude, miss.

09:27.000 --> 09:28.500
- Really?
- Yes. You know what?

09:28.500 --> 09:30.875
You need to make yourself
available for love

09:30.875 --> 09:32.500
before anything can love you.

09:32.500 --> 09:33.750
- Where did you read that?

09:33.750 --> 09:35.208
- Someone Lovished it to me.

09:35.208 --> 09:36.333
- They Lovished it to you?

09:36.333 --> 09:38.542
- Doesn t make it any less true.

09:38.542 --> 09:40.041
- I will take that
under advisement.

