10:44.375 --> 10:46.291
- Can I help you?
- Are you the vet?

10:46.291 --> 10:48.125
- I am.
- I have a-a dog in my car.

10:48.125 --> 10:49.250
She s very sick.
I need help.

10:49.250 --> 10:50.458
- Let s get her
to the exam room.

10:50.458 --> 10:52.750
Okay.

10:52.750 --> 10:55.041
Yeah, she s definitely bloated.

10:57.625 --> 11:00.250
He breathing s a bit labored.
What happened?

11:00.250 --> 11:02.834
- Um, she got into
some leftovers.

11:02.834 --> 11:04.875
It was an accident.

11:04.875 --> 11:06.917
She s not even my dog.

11:06.917 --> 11:09.959
I m dog-sitting for work.

11:11.750 --> 11:14.500
- Well, seems that she s
just overeaten.

11:14.500 --> 11:16.750
- So...

11:16.750 --> 11:17.875
she s not sick?

11:17.875 --> 11:20.667
- She gorged herself.

11:20.667 --> 11:23.333
Sometimes dogs this young
don t know when to stop eating,

11:23.333 --> 11:25.750
which is why you need
to measure out their food.

11:25.750 --> 11:28.500
Walking is good for her.
- Gotcha.

11:28.500 --> 11:30.875
Thank you so much.

11:30.875 --> 11:33.041
- Harrison. Curry.

11:33.041 --> 11:36.291
- Kelsey. Drummond.

11:36.291 --> 11:38.291
How much do I owe you
for telling me

11:38.291 --> 11:41.291
that she s
an emotional overeater?

11:41.291 --> 11:42.458
- Why don t you bring her back

11:42.458 --> 11:44.208
so I can give her
a full examination,

11:44.208 --> 11:45.959
make sure everything s okay?

11:45.959 --> 11:47.291
We can settle the bill then.

11:47.291 --> 11:49.125
- It would have to be late.
Like, after work?

11:49.125 --> 11:50.625
- That s fine.

11:50.625 --> 11:51.750
- Sounds good.

11:51.750 --> 11:53.792
Um...

11:53.792 --> 11:55.458
- Okay. I got you.

12:00.250 --> 12:02.291
- I thought that we were going
to figure out a way

12:02.291 --> 12:04.375
to divide our assets evenly.

12:04.375 --> 12:06.583
So far, I am just getting scraps
from the dinner plate.

12:06.583 --> 12:08.166
- Scraps?

12:08.166 --> 12:11.500
Six months out of the year
in Florida is not scraps.

12:11.500 --> 12:13.667
You don t appreciate anything
I ve done for you.

12:13.667 --> 12:15.750
- I love lakes.

12:15.750 --> 12:17.750
- Oh, no, I m not giving you
Jackson Hole.

12:17.750 --> 12:18.875
End of discussion.

12:18.875 --> 12:20.375
- You give me the lake house,

12:20.375 --> 12:22.709
this ends right here,
right now.

12:22.709 --> 12:25.291
- That house is my happy place.

12:25.291 --> 12:26.583
You don t even like to fish.

12:26.583 --> 12:27.583
- Maybe I ll start.

12:27.583 --> 12:31.083
Okay.

12:31.083 --> 12:34.000
If--if I give you Jackson Hole,

12:34.000 --> 12:36.792
you ll agree
to the rest of the terms?

12:36.792 --> 12:38.750
- Yes.

12:46.500 --> 12:47.750
No.

12:47.750 --> 12:48.709
- Ugh!
- Oh.

12:48.709 --> 12:49.709
Come...

12:53.750 --> 12:55.542
- The Ballentines
have six properties

12:55.542 --> 12:57.625
in three countries,
and both of their inheritances

12:57.625 --> 12:59.959
are included
in their assets.

12:59.959 --> 13:01.375
Why don t these people
sign prenups?

13:01.375 --> 13:02.875
- No, no one wants
to think about divorce

13:02.875 --> 13:04.250
before they get married.

13:04.250 --> 13:06.917
It s like acknowledging
the inevitable.

13:06.917 --> 13:09.333
- Houses, cars,
boats, stocks...

13:09.333 --> 13:11.375
These people have more money
and possessions

13:11.375 --> 13:13.083
than I would know
what to do with.

13:13.083 --> 13:15.500
So how s the dog-sitting going?

13:15.500 --> 13:16.875
- Oh, where to start?

13:16.875 --> 13:20.208
Um, Daisy has destroyed
my living room,

13:20.208 --> 13:22.250
and apparently
my most comfortable

13:22.250 --> 13:24.000
pair of shoes
are also the tastiest.

13:24.000 --> 13:25.333
- Mm, that sounds tough.

13:25.333 --> 13:27.583
- Yeah, and dogs are expensive.

13:27.583 --> 13:29.542
I ve already brought her
to the vet for tummy troubles,

13:29.542 --> 13:31.041
and those hours aren t billable.

13:31.041 --> 13:33.583
But Jason gave the task to me,

13:33.583 --> 13:36.917
and I am going to show him
that I am a team player.

13:40.625 --> 13:41.750
Hey.

13:41.750 --> 13:43.208
Did you get the new
Ballentine terms?

13:43.208 --> 13:44.959
- I just finished them.

13:44.959 --> 13:47.291
- No, no. The new-new one.

13:47.291 --> 13:48.583
- What new-new one?

13:48.583 --> 13:50.083
- Came in about 20 minutes ago.

13:50.083 --> 13:52.250
The husband had a suggestion
on our new stock division.

13:52.250 --> 13:53.750
- I ve just been working
on this last set an hour.

13:53.750 --> 13:55.041
- Check your emails.

13:58.041 --> 14:03.041
♪ ♪

14:05.500 --> 14:07.583
- But this is totally different.
When do you need it?

14:07.583 --> 14:09.125
- First thing.
- Jason.

14:09.125 --> 14:10.709
I told Michelle
I d be home for dinner.

14:10.709 --> 14:12.500
- Try the new Spanish diet.

14:12.500 --> 14:13.792
They don t eat
till midnight.

14:13.792 --> 14:14.625
- But it s not a schedule.

14:14.625 --> 14:17.041
It s a...

14:17.041 --> 14:18.458
diet.

14:20.125 --> 14:21.834
- Hey, may I help you?

14:21.834 --> 14:25.250
- Hello, I m Kelsey Drummond.
I m here with Daisy.

14:25.250 --> 14:27.875
- Ah, yes.
We re expecting you.

14:27.875 --> 14:29.583
I m Andre.
- Hi.

14:29.583 --> 14:31.625
- Dr. Curry s just in the back
finishing up on some work.

14:31.625 --> 14:32.875
- Not a worry.

14:32.875 --> 14:33.875
I was just noticing

14:33.875 --> 14:35.834
all of these articles
and awards.

14:35.834 --> 14:38.333
- Yeah, those are all
for Dr. Curry s therapy program.

14:38.333 --> 14:40.667
- Therapy?
- Yeah, he matches patients

14:40.667 --> 14:42.792
with animals to help them
heal and cope

14:42.792 --> 14:45.417
with, well, pretty much
anything that ails them.

14:45.417 --> 14:46.875
- Wow.

14:46.875 --> 14:49.583
- Miss Drummond.
Welcome back.

14:49.583 --> 14:50.625
Hope you haven t
been waiting long.

14:50.625 --> 14:51.625
- Oh, not at all.

14:51.625 --> 14:52.917
I was just admiring

14:52.917 --> 14:55.792
all of your
success stories.

14:55.792 --> 14:57.583
Is that you
with the mayor?

14:57.583 --> 14:59.500
- Oh, yeah.

14:59.500 --> 15:03.834
His brother was a marine
who suffered from PTSD.

15:03.834 --> 15:06.875
Nothing the company of
a Labrador couldn t help with.

15:06.875 --> 15:08.000
Should we head back?
- Yeah, sure.

15:08.000 --> 15:09.375
- All right.

15:09.375 --> 15:12.166
- Come on, Daisy.
- Hey, Daisy.

15:12.166 --> 15:13.542
So is she chipped?

15:13.542 --> 15:14.542
- Chipped?

15:14.542 --> 15:15.667
- Oh, here.

15:18.542 --> 15:20.166
Let s see.

15:23.333 --> 15:24.917
Oh, there it is.

15:24.917 --> 15:27.208
Looks like she has one.

15:27.208 --> 15:29.333
If she ever gets
lost and found,

15:29.333 --> 15:31.834
any shelter can use this
to contact her owner.

15:35.417 --> 15:37.583
Here. Try this.

15:37.583 --> 15:39.792
- Oh. Thanks.

15:39.792 --> 15:41.125
- Mm-hmm.

15:41.125 --> 15:43.208
So how did Daisy
come into your company?

15:43.208 --> 15:45.375
- I have to watch her for work.

15:45.375 --> 15:47.542
I m a divorce mediator.

15:47.542 --> 15:49.542
- A divorce mediator?

15:49.542 --> 15:50.917
I don t know what that is.

15:50.917 --> 15:52.875
- Mediation is how a couple

15:52.875 --> 15:54.417
can legally settle a divorce

15:54.417 --> 15:56.208
without a judge deciding
who gets what.

15:56.208 --> 15:58.125
- And how does Daisy
come into play?

15:58.125 --> 15:59.709
- It s a client s pet.

15:59.709 --> 16:03.792
I was asked to watch her
until a settlement is reached.

16:03.792 --> 16:06.834
I m hoping that it will
impress my boss.

16:06.834 --> 16:09.667
- The old "dog-sitting
to get ahead in work" tactic.

16:09.667 --> 16:11.333
- So the fate of my career

16:11.333 --> 16:13.208
rests on her furry
little shoulders.

16:13.208 --> 16:15.375
- And she looks great.

16:15.375 --> 16:19.875
She s got a great coat,
great teeth.

16:19.875 --> 16:22.417
You are in great shape,
Miss Daisy.

16:22.417 --> 16:23.542
Here we go.

16:27.250 --> 16:28.750
And she hasn t
eaten anything

16:28.750 --> 16:30.250
she s not supposed to,
has she?

16:30.250 --> 16:33.750
- Oh, nothing besides
my shoes and furniture.

16:33.750 --> 16:35.417
- Yeah, you re probably gonna
need to crate train her

16:35.417 --> 16:37.709
for a while since
she s new to your home.

16:37.709 --> 16:39.917
- I don t know how I m gonna get
through the next two months.

16:39.917 --> 16:42.750
- Well, I do help out with

16:42.750 --> 16:45.583
training and care assistance,
if you re interested.

16:45.583 --> 16:47.417
- I am interested.
- Okay.

16:47.417 --> 16:49.250
Well, then I can meet
this weekend.

16:49.250 --> 16:52.250
If you re available.
- I m available.

16:52.250 --> 16:54.417
- Okay.

16:54.417 --> 16:56.875
- Why are these properties
so important to them?

16:56.875 --> 16:58.166
- They re probably not.

16:58.166 --> 16:59.917
They probably just do it
to make the other suffer.

16:59.917 --> 17:02.291
You know how these couples are.
- Yeah.

17:02.291 --> 17:05.375
Well, we ll just have to get
started on the new terms.

17:05.375 --> 17:08.583
- Oh, there is
- the dog.

17:08.583 --> 17:09.791
- Does Mrs. Ballentine
want her

17:09.791 --> 17:11.125
to get the house
in Jackson Hole?

17:11.125 --> 17:14.709
- She just wants to make sure
the dog is fine.

17:14.709 --> 17:16.916
She is doing fine, right?

17:16.916 --> 17:19.959
- Oh, yeah, just tell
Mrs. Ballentine

17:19.959 --> 17:21.834
that she is good and healthy.

17:21.834 --> 17:23.791
- All right, well, she d like
to see for herself.

17:23.791 --> 17:25.416
- What, does she want to make
a house call or something?

17:25.416 --> 17:27.040
You have her information.

17:27.040 --> 17:29.125
Photos and videos
will suffice, so...

17:31.417 --> 17:33.667
All right, let s get back
to these terms.

17:36.250 --> 17:38.125
- Okay.

17:38.125 --> 17:39.792
- Daisy.

17:39.792 --> 17:42.041
You re not so bad.

17:42.041 --> 17:43.959
I don t know what Kelsey s
always complaining about.

17:43.959 --> 17:45.750
You re a good girl.

17:50.291 --> 17:52.500
Oh, my goodness.
What do you think?

17:52.500 --> 17:54.333
Should we talk to him
face-to-face?

17:54.333 --> 17:56.917
I mean webcam-to-webcam?

18:00.000 --> 18:02.792
- Hello. Finally.

18:02.792 --> 18:05.166
Hi, Fireman Randy.

18:05.166 --> 18:06.166
- You know, I got to admit,
you took a while

18:06.166 --> 18:07.375
to answer my video request.

18:07.375 --> 18:08.959
I thought maybe
you weren t interested.

18:08.959 --> 18:10.834
- Uh, no, actually,
you are the first person

18:10.834 --> 18:13.000
that I have ever Lovished.

18:13.000 --> 18:16.166
- So now that we ve spoken,
we should probably meet.

18:16.166 --> 18:17.375
I mean, it s kind of hard

18:17.375 --> 18:19.041
to make a connection
through a screen.

18:19.041 --> 18:21.166
- Uh, yeah.
That--that would be lovely.

18:21.166 --> 18:22.625
How about Thursday night?

18:22.625 --> 18:25.000
- Thursday it is.

18:25.000 --> 18:26.083
I know the perfect spot.

18:26.083 --> 18:27.667
- Great.
Email me when and where.

18:27.667 --> 18:28.709
Bye.

18:31.667 --> 18:32.875
Ah!

18:32.875 --> 18:35.417
♪ I have a date
with a fireman ♪

18:36.917 --> 18:39.041
- So she just keeps going.

18:39.041 --> 18:40.709
Should I stop her?

18:40.709 --> 18:43.542
- This is her walk,
so unless you re in a hurry,

18:43.542 --> 18:47.000
she ll let you know when she
wants to stop, Miss Drummond.

18:47.000 --> 18:48.208
- Okay, for starters,

18:48.208 --> 18:50.333
I appreciate you
sharing your expertise,

18:50.333 --> 18:52.875
but you ve got to stop with
the "Miss Drummond" stuff.

18:52.875 --> 18:55.250
My name is Kelsey.
- Sorry.

18:55.250 --> 18:57.000
All right, all right,
then please,

18:57.000 --> 18:58.333
feel free to call me Harrison.

18:58.333 --> 18:59.750
- Oh, well, I was going to,

18:59.750 --> 19:02.208
because we re peers,
and it s not the 1800s.

19:03.583 --> 19:05.208
- Oh.

19:05.208 --> 19:08.709
- Sorry. Work emails.
- No worries.

19:08.709 --> 19:10.625
- Weekends don t mean much
to my boss.

19:10.625 --> 19:12.291
- Aha, too many broken hearts?

19:12.291 --> 19:14.125
- Most of the time,
our clients

19:14.125 --> 19:16.208
are way past
the broken heart stage.

19:16.208 --> 19:17.959
They re in the, uh,

19:17.959 --> 19:19.834
"How much can I squeeze
out of this?" Phase.

19:19.834 --> 19:21.542
- Ooh, those don t sound
like fun phases.

19:21.542 --> 19:24.083
- No, but...

19:24.083 --> 19:26.041
everyone s got em.

19:26.041 --> 19:27.458
- Well, it seems like
your work has

19:27.458 --> 19:29.041
given you quite the outlook
on relationships.

19:29.041 --> 19:31.208
- Dr. Curry.
Good to see you.

19:31.208 --> 19:33.250
- Oh, hello,
Miss Reed, Scout.

19:33.250 --> 19:34.834
- How have you been?

19:34.834 --> 19:36.500
- Good, good.

19:36.500 --> 19:38.583
I m just here helping out
with some dog training.

19:38.583 --> 19:40.125
- Personal consultation?

19:40.125 --> 19:42.208
I didn t know you did those.

19:42.208 --> 19:43.709
I ll have to make
an appointment.

19:43.709 --> 19:45.500
- Oh, that shouldn t
be necessary.

19:45.500 --> 19:47.500
I don t think Scout
is causing too many problems.

19:50.583 --> 19:51.959
Have a good day.

19:54.000 --> 19:57.208
She s one of my clients.

19:57.208 --> 19:59.083
I was the one who found Scout
for her father.

19:59.083 --> 20:00.583
- Oh, so her father
is another

20:00.583 --> 20:02.291
successful patient
of the program?

20:02.291 --> 20:03.500
- That s right.

20:03.500 --> 20:05.458
- Quite the hero
in these parts.

20:05.458 --> 20:07.041
- I hate that term.

20:07.041 --> 20:09.542
Besides, it s really the animals
who are the heroes.

20:09.542 --> 20:11.250
Isn t that right, Daisy?

20:11.250 --> 20:14.583
They re the ones who are there
for people constantly,

20:14.583 --> 20:18.291
loyal without judgment,
and require nothing in return.

20:18.291 --> 20:19.667
- Except belly rubs
and liver treats.

20:19.667 --> 20:21.083
That s true.

20:21.083 --> 20:22.792
But that s still more
than you can say

20:22.792 --> 20:24.917
for most people, right?

20:24.917 --> 20:26.875
I m sure your work
has shown you that.

20:26.875 --> 20:29.542
- Oh, yes, plenty of times.

20:29.542 --> 20:32.500
- So it would be helpful
to come by your house

20:32.500 --> 20:34.792
just to see how Daisy is
in a home environment.

20:34.792 --> 20:36.875
- Uh, sure.
- Cool.

20:36.875 --> 20:38.709
- Oh, I almost forgot.

20:42.041 --> 20:43.542
- You documenting
the training?

20:43.542 --> 20:45.625
- Uh, it s for the owner.
- Ah.

20:45.625 --> 20:47.542
- Just to let her know
that everything s fine.

20:47.542 --> 20:48.875
- Ah. Yeah, you re fine.

20:48.875 --> 20:50.041
Everything s fine.

20:53.041 --> 20:56.500
♪ ♪

20:56.500 --> 20:58.125
- How long do these
blood tests take?

20:58.125 --> 21:00.417
- They re just making sure
they do it right.

21:00.417 --> 21:02.500
- Sorry for the wait.

21:02.500 --> 21:05.375
- It s fine.

21:05.375 --> 21:06.583
- So what s the news?

21:06.583 --> 21:08.333
Well--

21:08.333 --> 21:11.709
- I m just gonna put that
on vibrate.

21:11.709 --> 21:13.375
- So?

21:13.375 --> 21:16.208
- Well, here are
your blood tests.

21:19.792 --> 21:24.291
It means... you are going
to be parents.

21:24.291 --> 21:25.375
- So it s official?

21:25.375 --> 21:26.792
- Yes, it s official.

21:26.792 --> 21:28.083
Congratulations.

21:28.083 --> 21:29.959
- How far along?

21:29.959 --> 21:31.208
- About five weeks.

21:31.208 --> 21:34.583
- So we should expect
the baby in, like...

21:34.583 --> 21:36.208
- 35 weeks.

21:36.208 --> 21:38.083
Pregnancy lasts
40 weeks, Mitch.

21:38.083 --> 21:39.417
- Yeah, yeah,
I didn t know if you--

21:39.417 --> 21:40.959
I knew that.
I knew that.

21:47.208 --> 21:49.041
Look, I m sorry, work.

21:53.709 --> 21:55.583
- Maintaining
a good home environment

21:55.583 --> 21:58.917
is the most important aspect
of dog ownership.

21:58.917 --> 22:01.417
After all, it is where they
spend the most time.

22:03.834 --> 22:07.375
So you ll just want to secure
and hide any loose wires

22:07.375 --> 22:09.083
or cables that might be
lying around.

22:09.083 --> 22:11.000
Daisy ll want to chew
right through those.

22:11.000 --> 22:12.834
- I ll take care of that
right away.

22:12.834 --> 22:14.583
- And she s not left alone

22:14.583 --> 22:16.250
for too long during the day,
is she?

22:16.250 --> 22:18.375
Like when you re at work
or out?

22:18.375 --> 22:20.750
Dogs don t really like that,
especially at her age.

22:20.750 --> 22:23.333
- Well, when I m at work,
my mom comes by to check on her,

22:23.333 --> 22:26.333
and aside from the office,
I m pretty much always here.

22:26.333 --> 22:27.542
I don t really have
anywhere else to be.

22:29.166 --> 22:31.667
And saying that out loud
makes my life sound very sad.

22:31.667 --> 22:32.917
- No, no, no.

22:32.917 --> 22:34.750
I-I get it.

22:34.750 --> 22:36.458
I m the same way.

22:36.458 --> 22:39.625
I see you have a crate.
That s good.

22:39.625 --> 22:41.959
It ll help keep Daisy
from destroying things at night.

22:43.625 --> 22:46.041
Do you move it to the bedroom
when you go to bed?

22:46.041 --> 22:47.917
- Uh, no.
Should I?

22:47.917 --> 22:49.458
- Definitely.

22:49.458 --> 22:51.125
Dogs are social animals.

22:51.125 --> 22:52.625
They don t like to sleep alone.

22:52.625 --> 22:54.542
- Hmm.

22:54.542 --> 22:55.709
- Well, for the most part,

22:55.709 --> 22:58.458
your home looks
pretty accommodating for a dog.

22:58.458 --> 23:00.583
Just keep your clothes away
if you don t want them chewed on

23:00.583 --> 23:03.291
and make sure any food
is in a safe place.

23:03.291 --> 23:05.125
Wouldn t want another
cobbler incident.

23:05.125 --> 23:07.500
- Okay, that cobbler
would have gone uneaten

23:07.500 --> 23:09.959
if she didn t always
jump on everything.

23:09.959 --> 23:11.208
When can we train that out?

23:11.208 --> 23:12.667
I feel like every time
she sees me,

23:12.667 --> 23:13.834
she wants to jump on me.

23:13.834 --> 23:15.125
- Well, jumping is actually

23:15.125 --> 23:18.166
an instinctive display
of affection from a dog.

23:18.166 --> 23:19.834
When they re puppies,
they learn

23:19.834 --> 23:22.667
to lick their mother s
face and eyes.

23:22.667 --> 23:24.542
That s why Daisy
jumps on you.

23:24.542 --> 23:25.959
She just wants
to lick your face

23:25.959 --> 23:27.792
because she recognizes you
as her mother.

23:27.792 --> 23:29.417
- That actually sounds
kind of sweet.

23:29.417 --> 23:31.458
- Yeah.

23:31.458 --> 23:33.208
- I know she doesn t look
like a handful,

23:33.208 --> 23:36.709
but I wouldn t be able
to handle this without you.

23:36.709 --> 23:40.250
- It s no problem, really.

23:40.250 --> 23:41.458
Should we head
to the bedroom, then?

23:41.458 --> 23:43.917
- What?
- To move the crate in?

23:43.917 --> 23:46.250
- Oh, right. Yeah.

23:48.375 --> 23:50.000
- Lead the way.

23:56.959 --> 23:59.041
- Daisy, come here.

23:59.041 --> 24:02.375
Good girl.
Good girl.

24:02.375 --> 24:04.834
Oh, she s such a good girl.

24:04.834 --> 24:07.667
- Okay.

24:07.667 --> 24:10.875
There you go,
Mrs. Ballentine.

24:12.667 --> 24:15.041
Why does she respond to you
and not me?

24:15.041 --> 24:16.041
- I don t know.

24:16.041 --> 24:17.542
Maybe dogs can sense
conviction.

24:17.542 --> 24:18.750
Go.

24:18.750 --> 24:21.375
- Great, so I m without that?

24:21.375 --> 24:22.750
- What s up?
You look exhausted.

24:22.750 --> 24:25.166
- Just work, long day.

24:25.166 --> 24:26.583
- Well, it s not over yet.

24:26.583 --> 24:28.375
You need to walk Daisy.

24:28.375 --> 24:30.083
- Why can t you?

24:30.083 --> 24:31.500
- Oh, come on.

24:31.500 --> 24:32.834
What, do you think
I dressed this nice

24:32.834 --> 24:34.083
for you and the dog?

24:34.083 --> 24:36.166
- I do not judge
your fashion choices.

24:36.166 --> 24:38.000
- I have a date.
- A date?

24:38.000 --> 24:39.875
- Yes, and I am late enough
already as it is.

24:39.875 --> 24:41.250
Wish me luck.

24:41.250 --> 24:43.083
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

24:48.583 --> 24:52.000
- Well, it looks like we are
taking a walk, Daisy.

24:53.208 --> 24:55.417
- So I m just really nervous.

24:55.417 --> 24:57.792
- Oh, there s nothing
to be nervous about.

24:57.792 --> 24:59.583
- You would think, after so many
years of meeting people,

24:59.583 --> 25:00.792
that it would get easier, but--

25:00.792 --> 25:02.166
- It doesn t get easier,
does it?

25:02.166 --> 25:03.917
- No, no.

25:03.917 --> 25:07.417
Well, guess that s why
I resorted to online dating.

25:07.417 --> 25:09.291
So how about you?

25:09.291 --> 25:11.583
Why did you join
the Lovishness community?

25:13.500 --> 25:16.500
Uh, you know,
I guess I just wanted

25:16.500 --> 25:18.166
to find someone
to connect with.

25:18.166 --> 25:20.625
My husband passed away
about ten years ago,

25:20.625 --> 25:22.583
and, you know,
things were okay

25:22.583 --> 25:23.834
when my daughter
was living at home,

25:23.834 --> 25:25.458
but then she grew up.

25:25.458 --> 25:28.125
She moved out,
you know, and...

25:28.125 --> 25:30.041
I don t know. It just--
it gets hard being alone.

25:30.041 --> 25:31.792
- No, I get it.

25:31.792 --> 25:34.542
As a single father,
when my youngest left the nest,

25:34.542 --> 25:36.625
I honestly didn t know
what I was gonna do.

25:36.625 --> 25:38.000
I would--I actually
caught myself

25:38.000 --> 25:39.917
talking to an empty house.

25:39.917 --> 25:41.792
- Well, at least
you always know

25:41.792 --> 25:43.291
what your response
is gonna be, right?

25:43.291 --> 25:44.667
- Hmm?

25:44.667 --> 25:48.291
- Cause you were just talking
to yourself, so you--

25:48.291 --> 25:49.792
Oh, just forget it.

25:49.792 --> 25:51.417
It was a stupid joke.

25:54.250 --> 25:57.125
Um, so did you, uh--
did you find a way

25:57.125 --> 25:58.667
to help with the loneliness?

25:58.667 --> 26:00.125
- Well, actually,
I got a dalmatian,

26:00.125 --> 26:01.792
and now he s my best friend.

26:01.792 --> 26:03.041
- Come on.
- Yeah.

26:03.041 --> 26:05.250
- A fireman with a dalmatian?

26:05.250 --> 26:06.834
That is funny.

26:06.834 --> 26:08.500
- Why is that funny?

26:08.500 --> 26:11.333
- Well, cause the dalmatian.

26:11.333 --> 26:13.583
It s traditionally
the firehouse dog.

26:13.583 --> 26:15.166
- Right, right.

26:15.166 --> 26:17.834
I never made that connection.

26:22.917 --> 26:24.709
- Easy, girl, easy.

26:26.000 --> 26:27.709
Daisy, no!

26:34.917 --> 26:37.083
Okay, um...

26:38.917 --> 26:41.250
Answer.

26:41.250 --> 26:43.166
- Hi, you ve reached
the voice mail

26:43.166 --> 26:48.208
of Rhonda Drummond,
AKA Rhondagirl at Lovishness.

26:48.208 --> 26:50.375
Leave me a message,
and I ll get back to you

26:50.375 --> 26:52.125
if I find you worthy
of my attention.

26:53.750 --> 26:55.375
- Mom, why aren t you answering?

26:55.375 --> 26:56.375
I need you.

26:56.375 --> 26:58.625
Uh, okay, call me.

26:58.625 --> 26:59.875
Bye.

27:08.709 --> 27:10.542
- Harrison Curry.

27:10.542 --> 27:12.834
- Harrison, uh, it s--
it s Kelsey.

27:12.834 --> 27:14.625
I was walking Daisy
in my neighborhood,

27:14.625 --> 27:17.291
and she got away from me.

27:17.291 --> 27:18.709
I don t know what to do,

27:18.709 --> 27:21.458
and I didn t know
who else to call.

27:21.458 --> 27:23.166
- Well, don t worry.
I will be right over.

27:23.166 --> 27:24.542
I ll meet you at your place.

27:24.542 --> 27:25.542
- Okay, great.

27:25.542 --> 27:27.834
- No problem.

27:32.166 --> 27:35.083
- Shouldn t we go
to the shelter?

27:35.083 --> 27:36.834
Could we track
the microchip?

27:36.834 --> 27:38.709
- Microchip isn t a GPS.

27:38.709 --> 27:40.917
It ll only identify her
once she s found and turned in,

27:40.917 --> 27:43.417
and then they contact
who she s registered to.

27:43.417 --> 27:45.750
- That s the Ballentines.

27:45.750 --> 27:47.333
They can t know
that I ve lost her.

27:47.333 --> 27:49.208
- Hey, don t worry.

27:49.208 --> 27:51.083
We will find her, okay?

27:54.333 --> 27:57.417
- I just know that I ve lost her
and I have messed everything up.

27:57.417 --> 27:59.250
- You make these claims

27:59.250 --> 28:02.458
like you re so confident
with how things will be.

28:02.458 --> 28:03.792
- Is that bad?

28:03.792 --> 28:05.417
- No, no, no. No.

28:05.417 --> 28:07.250
But you can t always know

28:07.250 --> 28:10.166
how things
are gonna turn out.

28:10.166 --> 28:12.709
Like your clients,
none of them got married

28:12.709 --> 28:15.500
knowing it would end
in divorce.

28:15.500 --> 28:17.750
- Trust me, I have seen
plenty of couples

28:17.750 --> 28:19.917
where divorce
was no surprise.

28:19.917 --> 28:21.834
- Okay, maybe that was
a bad example.

28:21.834 --> 28:23.333
What about Daisy?

28:23.333 --> 28:24.834
- What about her?

28:24.834 --> 28:26.500
- Well, you didn t think
you d like Daisy,

28:26.500 --> 28:28.250
but now you re worried sick
about her,

28:28.250 --> 28:30.917
and I don t think
it s just because of work.

28:30.917 --> 28:32.125
- Wait a minute.

28:32.125 --> 28:34.125
We re back at my house.

28:34.125 --> 28:36.083
You took us in a circle?

28:36.083 --> 28:37.709
We re supposed to be looking
for Daisy.

28:37.709 --> 28:39.625
- I was just trying
to give it time.

28:39.625 --> 28:40.583
- Give what time?

28:43.583 --> 28:45.000
Daisy!

28:45.000 --> 28:49.125
Oh, how did you get back here?

28:49.125 --> 28:51.542
Oh, you re such a good girl!

28:51.542 --> 28:52.750
- See?

28:52.750 --> 28:54.250
Most dogs make their way home.

28:54.250 --> 28:56.417
- Thank you.

28:56.417 --> 28:57.875
I really appreciate it.

28:57.875 --> 28:59.000
- No problem.

29:02.458 --> 29:05.542
Uh, we should probably work
on leash training soon,

29:05.542 --> 29:07.125
make sure this doesn t
happen again.

29:07.125 --> 29:08.917
- Sounds good.

29:10.500 --> 29:12.125
Thanks again.

29:12.125 --> 29:13.125
- Night.

29:13.125 --> 29:14.000
- Night.

29:16.709 --> 29:17.792
Come on.

29:17.792 --> 29:19.667
Come on, Daisy.

29:21.375 --> 29:25.000
Okay.

29:25.000 --> 29:27.959
Oh.

29:30.458 --> 29:33.542
Oh, is this cause
you love me, Daisy?

29:33.542 --> 29:35.917
Oh, yeah, that--no,
that s getting a little gross.

29:35.917 --> 29:37.542
- Hey, is everything okay?

29:37.542 --> 29:39.375
I got your calls,
your messages.

29:39.375 --> 29:40.875
Is Daisy okay?

29:40.875 --> 29:42.500
- Oh, she s--she s right here.
She s fine.

29:42.500 --> 29:44.417
- Okay, what happened?

29:44.417 --> 29:46.375
Tell me more.
Tell me more.

29:46.375 --> 29:48.875
- I lost control of Daisy,
and she ran off,

29:48.875 --> 29:52.750
and I didn t know who else
to call, so I called the vet.

29:52.750 --> 29:56.834
We walked around and talked
until we got back here,

29:56.834 --> 29:58.583
and Daisy was waiting for us.

29:58.583 --> 30:00.333
- That s it?

30:00.333 --> 30:03.375
- Well, there s not really
anything else to share.

30:03.375 --> 30:05.375
Why don t you tell me
about your date?

30:05.375 --> 30:07.709
- Oh, sadly,
connecting online

30:07.709 --> 30:10.166
is not the same
as connecting in person.

30:10.166 --> 30:11.583
- Mom, I m sorry.

30:11.583 --> 30:12.917
- Eh, don t worry about it.

30:12.917 --> 30:15.041
I am much more interested
in what happened on your date.

30:15.041 --> 30:16.041
- Okay, it was not a date.

30:16.041 --> 30:17.250
- Oh, come on.

30:17.250 --> 30:18.792
A moonlight walk
around the neighborhood,

30:18.792 --> 30:20.917
talking and getting
to know each other?

30:20.917 --> 30:23.583
- That s just something
two people do.

30:23.583 --> 30:26.583
- It s also what a date is.

30:26.583 --> 30:28.375
It just felt
weirdly natural to you

30:28.375 --> 30:30.083
cause you didn t
take your list.

30:30.083 --> 30:36.583
♪ ♪

30:36.583 --> 30:39.875
- Okay, people, the Ballentines
will be back in a few days.

30:39.875 --> 30:41.542
We ll have to produce
something new.

30:41.542 --> 30:43.583
We may need
to start all over again

30:43.583 --> 30:45.041
and get everything in order

30:45.041 --> 30:46.875
to find something
that they will agree on.

30:46.875 --> 30:49.041
Be best to clear
your schedules.

30:49.041 --> 30:51.417
This is gonna take a while.

30:56.417 --> 30:57.917
Something more important, Mitch?

30:59.625 --> 31:01.375
- Of course not, sir.

31:01.375 --> 31:03.417
- Good.
Let s get to work, then.

31:16.458 --> 31:19.083
Oh, no.

31:19.083 --> 31:20.291
Stacee, look, I got to go.

31:20.291 --> 31:22.125
Tell Jason and Kelsey
it was an emergency.

31:22.125 --> 31:23.417
I think there might be
something wr--

31:23.417 --> 31:24.792
Uh, never mind.

31:24.792 --> 31:26.417
Michelle, what are you
doing here?

31:26.417 --> 31:27.458
- I couldn t reach you.

31:27.458 --> 31:29.834
- Look, what happened?
Is everything okay?

31:29.834 --> 31:33.291
- I had a--I felt an intense
abdominal pain earlier,

31:33.291 --> 31:35.250
and it really scared me.

31:35.250 --> 31:37.667
I took a taxi to the doctor
and then here.

31:37.667 --> 31:38.834
- So what is it?
Is the baby okay?

31:38.834 --> 31:40.583
- It was nothing.

31:40.583 --> 31:43.125
The doctor gave me and the baby
a clean bill of health.

31:43.125 --> 31:45.250
- Babe, that is--that s great.

31:45.250 --> 31:47.208
I m glad that you re both okay.

31:47.208 --> 31:48.667
- But I couldn t
reach you, Mitch.

31:48.667 --> 31:49.667
- Now, I know. I know.

31:49.667 --> 31:51.083
And I ve been
in a meeting all day,

31:51.083 --> 31:52.834
and I ve just not had
a chance to respond.

31:52.834 --> 31:54.709
- Things are different
now that we re having a baby.

31:54.709 --> 31:56.500
I need to know I can reach you.

31:56.500 --> 31:58.917
- I m sorry.

31:58.917 --> 32:01.166
You--you are
absolutely right.

32:01.166 --> 32:02.709
I m gonna talk to Jason.

32:02.709 --> 32:04.000
I ll explain to him
my situation,

32:04.000 --> 32:05.834
and he ll understand.

32:07.875 --> 32:10.709
Sweetheart, I will never

32:10.709 --> 32:15.166
miss another call, okay?

32:15.166 --> 32:16.166
Now come here.

32:16.166 --> 32:17.500
Both of you come over here.

32:17.500 --> 32:19.083
Come here.

32:22.125 --> 32:23.375
♪ ♪

32:25.792 --> 32:27.041
It s here.

32:27.041 --> 32:28.542
- Oh, shoot, they mailed it?

32:28.542 --> 32:29.875
- So?

32:29.875 --> 32:32.625
- Well, they only mail bad news.

32:32.625 --> 32:35.125
Good news, you call
and congratulate the person.

32:35.125 --> 32:36.875
Bad news, they send you a letter

32:36.875 --> 32:38.542
and never have
to deal with you again.

32:38.542 --> 32:41.709
- Yeah, but they also mail
checks, so...

32:41.709 --> 32:43.375
- I m not, no.

32:43.375 --> 32:45.041
This is my life s work.

32:45.041 --> 32:46.709
You read it.

32:46.709 --> 32:48.417
- Oh, so you re gonna make me
the bearer of bad news?

32:48.417 --> 32:49.709
- So you think
it s bad news too?

32:49.709 --> 32:50.959
- Fine.

32:50.959 --> 32:52.208
I ll get this over with

32:52.208 --> 32:53.583
if you re gonna be a baby
about it.

32:58.875 --> 33:00.041
- Well?

33:00.041 --> 33:02.583
- So, uh,

33:02.583 --> 33:05.875
they didn t approve
the grant increase.

33:05.875 --> 33:07.250
- But without more money,

33:07.250 --> 33:09.375
we won t be able
to function properly.

33:09.375 --> 33:10.875
- They noticed that too,

33:10.875 --> 33:14.208
which is why they decided
to deny us a grant completely.

33:14.208 --> 33:15.208
- What?

33:15.208 --> 33:16.250
- Yeah, apparently they feel

33:16.250 --> 33:17.875
that if the money
they can provide

33:17.875 --> 33:20.500
isn t enough for our uses,
it d be more helpful elsewhere.

33:20.500 --> 33:22.250
- Ugh.
- I m sorry.

33:22.250 --> 33:23.917
See, that--that s why I didn t
want to be the one to read it.

33:25.000 --> 33:26.750
So what now?

33:26.750 --> 33:28.709
- There are other foundations,
and there are other grants.

33:28.709 --> 33:30.083
We ll figure it out.

33:30.083 --> 33:31.875
This clinic hasn t closed yet,

33:31.875 --> 33:34.583
so right now,
it s business as usual.

33:34.583 --> 33:36.750
- All right, you got it, boss.

33:43.750 --> 33:46.125
So most dogs
will pull on their leash

33:46.125 --> 33:48.959
because they re full
of excess energy,

33:48.959 --> 33:50.875
so before we start
walking Daisy,

33:50.875 --> 33:52.792
it ll be helpful
to just play some fetch

33:52.792 --> 33:53.959
or let her run around.

33:57.417 --> 34:01.959
Uh, sorry, I should
probably take this.

34:01.959 --> 34:03.875
Hello?
- Dr. Curry, it s Ranger.

34:03.875 --> 34:05.166
- Okay, what s wrong?

34:05.166 --> 34:06.625
- I don t know.
He s not himself.

34:06.625 --> 34:08.250
He s acting really strange.
Please hurry.

34:08.250 --> 34:09.750
- Okay. No, I will be
right over.

34:09.750 --> 34:10.833
- Thank you so much.
I appreciate it.

34:10.833 --> 34:11.875
- Bye.

34:13.792 --> 34:17.333
I am really sorry,
but I m gonna have to go.

34:17.333 --> 34:19.041
A military veteran
that s part of my program

34:19.041 --> 34:21.166
is worried about
his therapy dog.

34:21.166 --> 34:23.458
So can we maybe
do this another day?

34:23.458 --> 34:26.166
- Oh, yeah, no problem.

34:26.166 --> 34:29.375
But we did
drive here together.

34:29.375 --> 34:30.750
- Well, would you mind
coming along?

34:30.750 --> 34:31.833
- Of course not.

34:31.833 --> 34:33.041
I mean, if it s an emergency.

34:33.041 --> 34:34.208
- Yeah, thank you.
- Yeah.

34:34.208 --> 34:36.208
- Thank you, and it shouldn t
be too long.

34:36.208 --> 34:37.708
- Come on, Daisy.

34:44.250 --> 34:45.333
- Come in.

34:47.458 --> 34:49.708
- Hey, Mr. Levy.

34:49.708 --> 34:53.417
This is, uh, Kelsey Drummond
and Daisy.

34:53.417 --> 34:56.000
- Dr. Curry, thank you so much
for coming.

34:56.000 --> 34:57.417
I didn t know
what else to do.

34:57.417 --> 34:59.709
- Not a problem,
not a problem.

34:59.709 --> 35:03.667
Let s take a look
and see how Ranger s doing.

35:03.667 --> 35:05.000
- He just started
coughing today,

35:05.000 --> 35:06.834
and I don t know why.

35:06.834 --> 35:09.917
- Does it happen often?
- Yeah, I think.

35:09.917 --> 35:12.208
I m not that sure.

35:12.208 --> 35:13.542
- Okay, all right,
let s take a listen.

35:13.542 --> 35:16.208
Hey, bud.

35:16.208 --> 35:18.041
Just as I thought.

35:18.041 --> 35:20.709
That cough sounds familiar.

35:20.709 --> 35:22.166
Have you taken him
anywhere recently

35:22.166 --> 35:23.542
where there were other dogs?

35:23.542 --> 35:25.375
- He was at the groomer s
a couple of days ago.

35:25.375 --> 35:28.208
- Okay, sounds like he caught
kennel cough.

35:28.208 --> 35:30.333
It s highly contagious,
but it s very common.

35:30.333 --> 35:32.333
It s not a serious problem
at all.

35:32.333 --> 35:35.375
Has he been eating well
and acting like himself?

35:35.375 --> 35:36.542
- Yeah.

35:36.542 --> 35:38.166
- Okay, then he should
be better in about a week,

35:38.166 --> 35:39.250
but I ll get you
some antibiotics

35:39.250 --> 35:41.709
just in case, all right?

35:41.709 --> 35:43.000
Where s his crate?

35:43.000 --> 35:44.333
- It s in the bedroom.

35:44.333 --> 35:46.208
- Okay, why don t you take him
there to rest,

35:46.208 --> 35:47.166
and I ll be right behind you?

35:47.166 --> 35:48.625
- Okay.
- All right.

35:58.375 --> 36:00.750
Everything okay?

36:00.750 --> 36:02.834
- I m just amazed

36:02.834 --> 36:05.834
to see someone
care so much for their pet.

36:05.834 --> 36:07.250
- Why?

36:07.250 --> 36:09.250
- I ve never been much
of an animal person.

36:09.250 --> 36:11.375
- Well, Mr. Levy suffers
from combat trauma.

36:11.375 --> 36:14.333
Ranger is his calming influence

36:14.333 --> 36:16.375
when Mr. Levy s
anxiety levels increase.

36:16.375 --> 36:18.709
- I get that,

36:18.709 --> 36:21.458
but they are
different species.

36:21.458 --> 36:23.291
They can t communicate.

36:23.291 --> 36:26.000
It s not like they have
anything in common.

36:26.000 --> 36:28.834
- Relationships don t come
from commonality.

36:28.834 --> 36:34.125
I mean, thinking that love would
come out of something like,

36:34.125 --> 36:37.792
I don t know,
a list of interests,

36:37.792 --> 36:38.792
I mean, that would be crazy.

36:38.792 --> 36:41.041
- Oh, yeah, totally crazy.

36:41.041 --> 36:42.375
- Yeah.

36:45.875 --> 36:47.875
- So where do you think
it comes from?

36:47.875 --> 36:50.917
- Oh, I don t know.

36:50.917 --> 36:53.125
Something deeper.

36:53.125 --> 36:55.500
But I m not the right person
to ask about this stuff.

36:55.500 --> 36:57.083
- Why s that?

36:57.083 --> 37:00.041
- Honestly, I-I feel like
I connect with animals more

37:00.041 --> 37:04.792
because they don t hide
who they are or how they feel,

37:04.792 --> 37:06.000
kind of like you.

37:06.000 --> 37:08.542
- So I m like a dog?

37:08.542 --> 37:10.834
- No, I just meant you--
you re straightforward,

37:10.834 --> 37:12.333
easy to understand.

37:12.333 --> 37:14.083
- Doc?
- Uh, yeah.

37:14.083 --> 37:15.750
- Duty calls, hero.

37:22.208 --> 37:23.583
Uh, just give me a minute
and we re good to go.

37:35.834 --> 37:42.083
♪ ♪

37:42.083 --> 37:44.500
- This is taking forever.

37:44.500 --> 37:46.500
- You late for something?

37:46.500 --> 37:48.500
- I was just trying to get home
at a decent hour.

37:48.500 --> 37:49.834
I feel like Michelle
feels like

37:49.834 --> 37:51.542
she s without a husband
right now.

37:51.542 --> 37:53.875
- Oh, I m sure she understands
how demanding work s been.

37:53.875 --> 37:55.875
- Yeah, I j--I m just--
I m spent.

37:55.875 --> 37:57.250
I d rather be home
with Michelle.

37:57.250 --> 37:58.792
- We still need
to completely reevaluate

37:58.792 --> 38:00.125
the Ballentine assets.

38:00.125 --> 38:01.959
- What about
a change of scenery?

38:01.959 --> 38:02.875
- Ooh, I don t know.

38:02.875 --> 38:04.458
Restaurants are dangerous.

38:04.458 --> 38:06.041
The last time we tried
to work at one,

38:06.041 --> 38:07.333
the waiter spilled
kung pao chicken

38:07.333 --> 38:09.542
all over
the financial documents,

38:09.542 --> 38:12.208
and chili peppers
were dropping out of the files

38:12.208 --> 38:15.208
at a meeting a week later.

38:15.208 --> 38:17.542
I m pretty sure that s why
we had the ant problem.

38:17.542 --> 38:19.500
- Yeah, so that s not
what I had in mind.

38:19.500 --> 38:21.208
Um, I was thinking maybe

38:21.208 --> 38:22.458
we could just work
from my house.

38:22.458 --> 38:24.709
- It s okay with me
if it is with Michelle.

38:24.709 --> 38:26.500
- Of course. I ll call her,
give her a heads-up.

38:26.500 --> 38:28.333
I get to spend time
with my lovely wife.

38:28.333 --> 38:29.458
You get a home-cooked meal.

38:29.458 --> 38:30.458
Then we hammer out
the new terms.

38:30.458 --> 38:33.166
- Done.

38:33.166 --> 38:39.709
♪ ♪

38:40.709 --> 38:42.041
Honey, I m home.

38:42.041 --> 38:45.750
Kelsey, good to see you again.

38:45.750 --> 38:48.417
- You too.

38:48.417 --> 38:49.709
- Let me help you with that.

38:49.709 --> 38:52.166
- Oh, thanks.
- Manners, I m so sorry.

38:53.834 --> 38:56.417
- Good to see you.
- Good to see you.

38:56.417 --> 38:57.709
Mm.

39:00.000 --> 39:01.125
- Uh, let me take your stuff.

39:01.125 --> 39:02.500
- Sure.

39:02.500 --> 39:04.083
- And I ll be right back.

39:04.083 --> 39:05.709
- So how s work?

39:05.709 --> 39:07.333
Must be busy,
from what I can tell.

39:07.333 --> 39:10.083
- I assume that you ve heard
about our difficult clients?

39:10.083 --> 39:12.125
I ve been told.

39:12.125 --> 39:13.750
Come on, dinner s almost ready.

39:13.750 --> 39:15.542
- Something smells good.

39:17.875 --> 39:19.750
Well, I m glad
that your students

39:19.750 --> 39:21.959
aren t as rambunctious
as Mitch was when he was a kid.

39:21.959 --> 39:23.625
- Oh, you and me both.

39:23.625 --> 39:25.166
- I was not that bad.

39:25.166 --> 39:27.291
How about you?

39:27.291 --> 39:28.667
Mitch told me
all about the dog.

39:28.667 --> 39:29.875
How s it been?

39:29.875 --> 39:31.583
- It started out rough,

39:31.583 --> 39:34.000
bad dog pun not intended.

39:34.000 --> 39:35.375
- When do you have
to give her back?

39:35.375 --> 39:37.500
- Soon.

39:41.041 --> 39:42.208
- Is everything all right?

39:42.208 --> 39:43.667
- I guess I m just

39:43.667 --> 39:46.041
getting used
to having her around,

39:46.041 --> 39:49.625
which is weird cause I never
pictured myself with a dog.

39:49.625 --> 39:53.000
- Guess you never know
how life s gonna turn out.

39:53.000 --> 39:54.000
- More coffee?

39:54.000 --> 39:55.917
- I m good.

39:55.917 --> 39:58.041
Um, you re not having any?

39:58.041 --> 39:59.625
- Oh, no, I probably
shouldn t have any.

39:59.625 --> 40:00.709
- Shouldn t?

40:00.709 --> 40:03.625
What, are you pregnant
or something?

40:05.333 --> 40:07.417
Wait, are you?

40:07.417 --> 40:08.917
- We weren t going
to tell anybody

40:08.917 --> 40:10.542
since it s still so soon.

40:10.542 --> 40:12.792
- Oh, congratulations!

40:12.792 --> 40:14.000
- Thank you.

40:14.000 --> 40:17.125
- Wow, so...

40:17.125 --> 40:19.709
work, marriage,
and a kid, huh?

40:19.709 --> 40:21.166
How are your juggling skills?

40:23.375 --> 40:25.083
Sorry, something I said?

40:28.041 --> 40:29.875
- Not at all.

40:29.875 --> 40:31.417
- We should get started.

40:34.000 --> 40:40.959
♪ ♪

41:04.375 --> 41:06.417
I already tried
the art collection.

41:06.417 --> 41:08.083
Lucy wanted
the postmodern pieces.

41:08.083 --> 41:09.208
Then it started
this whole debate

41:09.208 --> 41:11.583
over what constituted
postmodern.

41:11.583 --> 41:14.000
- It sounds like late nights
freshman year of college.

41:14.000 --> 41:15.208
- Sounds like
your college experience

41:15.208 --> 41:16.500
was different than mine.

41:16.500 --> 41:18.542
- Are these two gonna find
common ground on anything?

41:18.542 --> 41:20.250
- I think the only thing
they agree on is divorce.

41:20.250 --> 41:21.709
- What if they haven t
agreed on that?

41:21.709 --> 41:23.041
- What do you mean?

41:23.041 --> 41:24.417
- These sessions
are the only thing

41:24.417 --> 41:26.458
that s bringing
these two together.

41:26.458 --> 41:28.083
After this is all over,

41:28.083 --> 41:30.458
they ll be completely out
of each other s lives.

41:30.458 --> 41:33.250
What if Lucy
is turning down every option

41:33.250 --> 41:36.875
because she doesn t
want that to happen?

41:36.875 --> 41:38.792
- So she s unable
to finalize the divorce

41:38.792 --> 41:40.250
cause she doesn t want
to get divorced.

41:40.250 --> 41:42.083
- I mean, they each
have enough money

41:42.083 --> 41:44.208
to replace anything they lose.

41:44.208 --> 41:47.041
These physical objects
and properties

41:47.041 --> 41:50.583
are essentially meaningless.

41:50.583 --> 41:52.709
What if the one thing
that Lucy doesn t want to lose

41:52.709 --> 41:53.750
is her husband?

41:53.750 --> 41:55.250
- After spending
all that time with them,

41:55.250 --> 41:59.417
more than any other client,
do you really believe that?

41:59.417 --> 42:01.625
I think the only thing
they have in common is money.

42:01.625 --> 42:05.417
- Well, relationships
don t come from commonality.

42:05.417 --> 42:09.959
There s an unexplainable
and emotional connection,

42:09.959 --> 42:11.667
an understanding.

42:11.667 --> 42:13.291
- Huh, and where did that
come from?

42:16.375 --> 42:17.375
But listen,
whatever the solution,

42:17.375 --> 42:18.709
I hope you find it.

42:18.709 --> 42:20.750
You know you have
my recommendation for partner,

42:20.750 --> 42:23.834
but Jason s got a lot of stock
riding on this client,

42:23.834 --> 42:26.417
and, um, I don t know
how things will go

42:26.417 --> 42:28.750
if we don t make them happy.

42:28.750 --> 42:30.458
All right, listen,
that s enough for tonight.

42:30.458 --> 42:32.917
It s getting late.

42:32.917 --> 42:34.709
- Sounds good.
I ll show myself out.

42:34.709 --> 42:36.041
- Oh, boy.

42:38.792 --> 42:40.959
I will see you tomorrow.

42:46.875 --> 42:50.041
- Did you figure
everything out?

42:50.041 --> 42:52.125
- We re getting there.

42:52.125 --> 42:53.458
- So it s still going
to be a while

42:53.458 --> 42:55.333
until I get my husband back?

42:55.333 --> 42:57.959
- I don t think you need
to worry about that so much.

42:57.959 --> 43:02.166
Mitch loves you
more than anyone ever.

43:02.166 --> 43:03.375
I don t think I ve met

43:03.375 --> 43:06.500
a more perfect couple
than the two of you,

43:06.500 --> 43:08.750
and I don t think being
overworked changes that.

43:08.750 --> 43:10.583
- Sure gets in the way,
though.

43:10.583 --> 43:13.709
- If anyone can get through it,
it s you and Mitch,

43:13.709 --> 43:17.333
and you are gonna make
amazing parents.

43:19.583 --> 43:24.166
Oh, thank you.

43:24.166 --> 43:26.333
- Anytime.

43:30.041 --> 43:33.417
Hey, Mom.
- Hey.

43:33.417 --> 43:35.917
- Thanks again
for watching Daisy tonight.

43:35.917 --> 43:38.542
- Oh, not a problem.

43:38.542 --> 43:40.750
- I ll try not to have
another late night like this

43:40.750 --> 43:43.458
so you can go on more
Loverly dates

43:43.458 --> 43:45.542
or whatever they re called.

43:45.542 --> 43:48.375
- Yeah, well,
don t worry about it.

43:48.375 --> 43:50.458
I m not sure how much longer
I m willing to try that.

43:50.458 --> 43:51.792
- Why not?

43:51.792 --> 43:53.709
I thought you were
having fun with it.

43:53.709 --> 43:56.709
- Yeah, I mean, it s fun,
but it is so hard

43:56.709 --> 43:59.375
to find compatibility
through computers.

43:59.375 --> 44:01.375
- I thought that s how those
website and apps worked.

44:02.709 --> 44:05.375
Yeah, sweetie, but love does not
come from a checklist.

44:05.375 --> 44:07.542
- That is what everyone
keeps telling me.

44:07.542 --> 44:09.834
- I just want to find someone
I have a connection with.

44:09.834 --> 44:12.083
- Um, hello?

44:12.083 --> 44:14.333
Flesh and blood
sitting right next to you.

44:14.333 --> 44:16.750
- Yes, and I love you,
and you know it.

44:16.750 --> 44:18.500
I could not ask
for a better friend,

44:18.500 --> 44:21.166
but you also know that s not
the type I m talking about.

44:21.166 --> 44:23.667
- I know.

44:23.667 --> 44:25.041
- You know,
I never tell you this,

44:25.041 --> 44:28.417
but, um, one of the main reasons
I have no problem

44:28.417 --> 44:30.000
coming and helping you
with Daisy is,

44:30.000 --> 44:34.083
I hate being all alone
in my own place.

44:34.083 --> 44:36.750
- Mom, I didn t know that.

44:36.750 --> 44:40.083
You know that you can
come over here anytime

44:40.083 --> 44:41.542
as long as you call first.

44:41.542 --> 44:44.208
- Ugh.

44:44.208 --> 44:45.333
- Hey, how about
you stick around

44:45.333 --> 44:46.583
and we ll put on a movie?

44:46.583 --> 44:50.208
- Yes.
I will go make popcorn.

44:57.458 --> 44:58.917
- Mrs. Ballentine.

44:58.917 --> 45:00.250
- Ms. Ballentine.

45:00.250 --> 45:02.792
- Of course, Ms. Ballentine.

45:02.792 --> 45:07.166
- Well, I just came from another
unsuccessful meeting,

45:07.166 --> 45:10.500
and I thought I would just
stop by and ask about Daisy.

45:10.500 --> 45:12.417
The videos you ve been sending
have been great.

45:12.417 --> 45:15.250
- I m glad that you ve
enjoyed them,

45:15.250 --> 45:18.125
and Daisy is doing just fine.

45:18.125 --> 45:19.333
- Good to hear.

45:19.333 --> 45:21.000
- And I know that we ve yet
to come to terms

45:21.000 --> 45:22.458
that everybody can agree on,

45:22.458 --> 45:25.834
but I am still hard at work
figuring it out for you.

45:25.834 --> 45:28.917
- Well, thank you.

45:28.917 --> 45:31.667
- Ms. Ballentine?

45:31.667 --> 45:35.959
I know that it s not my place
to comment on your relationship,

45:35.959 --> 45:39.125
but can I ask you something?

45:39.125 --> 45:42.667
- Sure.

45:42.667 --> 45:44.917
- Are you sure that divorce
is right for you?

45:47.166 --> 45:51.792
- I mean, I know that your
relationship seems broken,

45:51.792 --> 45:56.166
but is there a reason you can t
agree on how to end it?

46:01.125 --> 46:03.834
Because maybe
you don t want to?

46:09.208 --> 46:10.709
- Well, that is not
what I expected

46:10.709 --> 46:12.375
a divorce mediator to say.

46:12.375 --> 46:17.375
- Well, I ve--
I ve learned a lot recently,

46:17.375 --> 46:19.750
changed my perspective,

46:19.750 --> 46:23.208
and I think, if you re having
doubts about everything,

46:23.208 --> 46:25.583
you should probably
talk to him about it.

46:29.333 --> 46:31.542
He might feel the same way.

46:31.542 --> 46:32.834
- Noted.

46:35.583 --> 46:38.333
Do I owe the firm anything
for this consultation?

46:38.333 --> 46:39.667
- Free of charge.

46:39.667 --> 46:41.041
- Hmm.

46:46.709 --> 46:51.208
♪ ♪

46:55.208 --> 46:56.583
- Mitch, this is your reminder

46:56.583 --> 46:58.041
about the appointment
with the doctor.

46:58.041 --> 47:00.166
- Thanks, Stacee.

47:05.583 --> 47:07.834
- Hey, Mitch.
You got a second?

47:07.834 --> 47:10.208
- I m heading out to that
appointment I told you about.

47:10.208 --> 47:11.917
- Of course,
but the partners and I

47:11.917 --> 47:13.875
are gonna have a quick meeting
about the Ballentines

47:13.875 --> 47:16.875
and the possibility
of bringing in a new partner.

47:16.875 --> 47:18.667
- Really?

47:18.667 --> 47:20.834
- Bringing in a new partner
will help lighten up the load.

47:20.834 --> 47:22.375
- I really got
to get going, though.

47:22.375 --> 47:24.709
- I promise it ll be quick.
Come on.

47:25.792 --> 47:32.709
♪ ♪

47:39.041 --> 47:40.625
- Hey, how is everything?

47:40.625 --> 47:41.875
- You missed the appointment,

47:41.875 --> 47:43.041
and I had to take
a taxi again.

47:43.041 --> 47:44.375
- Yeah, I know--

47:44.375 --> 47:45.583
- Since my car s
in the shop, remember?

47:45.583 --> 47:46.500
- I know,
and I m--I m so sorry.

47:46.500 --> 47:48.041
But I m--hey, hey.

47:48.041 --> 47:51.250
But I m here now.

47:56.834 --> 47:59.041
Look, I was on my way out
when Jason pulled me

47:59.041 --> 48:01.291
into a meeting to discuss
bringing on a new partner.

48:01.291 --> 48:02.625
This is a good thing.

48:02.625 --> 48:05.125
Bringing on a new partner
will--will give me more time.

48:05.125 --> 48:06.792
- But you promised you wouldn t
miss the appointment.

48:06.792 --> 48:08.333
- Once a new partner is chosen,

48:08.333 --> 48:09.291
I ll never miss
an appointment again.

48:09.291 --> 48:10.458
Look, things will settle down.

48:10.458 --> 48:12.041
- Until they pick back up again.

48:12.041 --> 48:14.166
- Look, babe, that s--that s
just the way work is sometimes.

48:14.166 --> 48:15.000
It s busy, and then it s not.

48:15.000 --> 48:16.166
- I know how hard you work,

48:16.166 --> 48:17.500
but I need my husband.

48:21.709 --> 48:23.417
- So where are we?

48:23.417 --> 48:28.667
- We re, um, heading home.

48:31.667 --> 48:37.208
♪ ♪

48:38.917 --> 48:45.500
♪ ♪

48:45.500 --> 48:46.667
- Hey, Andre.

48:46.667 --> 48:47.834
- Hey, Kelsey.

48:47.834 --> 48:49.166
Where s Daisy?

48:49.166 --> 48:50.542
- At home.

48:50.542 --> 48:52.750
I m actually here
for a different matter.

48:52.750 --> 48:54.166
- Oh, really?

48:54.166 --> 48:56.375
- I would like to look
at your felines, please.

48:56.375 --> 48:59.166
- Hmm, trying to find
a little friend for Daisy, huh?

48:59.166 --> 49:03.041
You know there s this old saying
about dogs and cats.

49:03.041 --> 49:05.625
- The cat actually
isn t for me.

49:05.625 --> 49:09.291
It s a gift for someone
who could use the company.

49:09.291 --> 49:12.208
- Giving someone
a living animal as a gift?

49:12.208 --> 49:14.375
Eh, kind of a risky move.

49:14.375 --> 49:15.917
- I m willing to take that risk.

49:20.667 --> 49:23.125
Hey, Harrison.

49:23.125 --> 49:25.792
Harrison.

49:25.792 --> 49:27.166
- Oh.
- Hello.

49:27.166 --> 49:29.166
How are you?
- I m fine.

49:29.166 --> 49:30.166
- Are you okay?
You seem a bit off.

49:30.166 --> 49:32.333
- No, I m fine.

49:33.709 --> 49:35.667
Just preoccupied.

49:35.667 --> 49:38.458
- Hey, Amy, would you mind
taking Miss Drummond here

49:38.458 --> 49:40.000
to the back
to check out some cats?

49:40.000 --> 49:41.291
- Sure.

49:41.291 --> 49:42.333
- I ll be right there
to help you.

49:42.333 --> 49:43.750
- Okay, sounds good.

49:45.917 --> 49:48.083
- What is with you, man?

49:48.083 --> 49:49.750
- Just a bit distracted.

49:49.750 --> 49:52.750
Been on the phone all day
with foundations about grants

49:52.750 --> 49:54.083
and then trying to see
if there s any way

49:54.083 --> 49:55.667
I can shrink the budget.

49:55.667 --> 49:58.750
- Well, why don t you
talk to her about it?

49:58.750 --> 50:02.417
- We don t need to bother
anybody else with this, okay?

50:02.417 --> 50:05.417
It s gonna be just fine.

50:05.417 --> 50:06.917
- Okay.

50:06.917 --> 50:09.041
- Okay.

50:09.041 --> 50:10.583
- Here you go, kiddo.

50:11.583 --> 50:14.083
- Hey, Mom.
- Hey.

50:14.083 --> 50:15.875
Oh, what you got there?

50:17.083 --> 50:19.834
- This little man

50:19.834 --> 50:21.834
is for you.

50:21.834 --> 50:23.250
- It s not another fireman,
is it?

50:26.625 --> 50:31.875
- Oh, my goodness,
he s adorable.

50:33.125 --> 50:34.583
- After we talked
the other night,

50:34.583 --> 50:36.625
I thought that maybe
you could use a friend,

50:36.625 --> 50:38.875
especially since Daisy s
leaving soon.

50:38.875 --> 50:42.917
- Honey, thank you.

50:42.917 --> 50:44.750
Wait, does this make me
a cat lady?

50:44.750 --> 50:48.458
- It makes you
a lady with a cat?

50:48.458 --> 50:49.709
- Okay, I can live with that.

50:49.709 --> 50:50.917
- I think you need
at least two more

50:50.917 --> 50:52.792
before you can join
the cat lady club.

50:52.792 --> 50:56.959
- Wait, I was lonely,
so you got me a pet?

50:56.959 --> 50:58.625
Does this mean you re starting
to get the beauty

50:58.625 --> 51:00.250
of connecting with something?

51:00.250 --> 51:03.834
- I guess my experience
with Daisy

51:03.834 --> 51:06.959
has changed my perspective.

51:06.959 --> 51:09.250
But don t start
with the "I told you so."

51:09.250 --> 51:10.959
- Oh, please, Kelsey,
I m your mother.

51:10.959 --> 51:12.125
I raised you.

51:12.125 --> 51:13.458
Every minute of your life

51:13.458 --> 51:15.417
is an "I told you so"
moment for me.

51:15.417 --> 51:17.959
Now this little guy and I,
we got to go to the store

51:17.959 --> 51:21.542
and get you some treats,
make you nice and fat,

51:21.542 --> 51:24.041
some little toys,
ooh, some cute little clothes.

51:24.041 --> 51:25.625
- No, no, no, don t do that.

51:25.625 --> 51:28.583
Don t be that person
who buys their pet clothes.

51:28.583 --> 51:31.250
- I m gonna get
matching outfits for myself.

51:31.250 --> 51:33.250
- I have made
a terrible mistake.

51:33.250 --> 51:34.458
- And, Kelsey?

51:34.458 --> 51:35.458
- Yeah, Mom?

51:35.458 --> 51:37.083
- Told you so.

51:42.625 --> 51:44.375
- Hmm.

51:44.375 --> 51:46.208
Hmm.

51:46.208 --> 51:49.291
Hmm.

51:49.291 --> 51:50.500
No.

51:50.500 --> 51:51.792
- Oh, come on.

51:51.792 --> 51:53.625
- What, did Kelsey not
write it down correctly?

51:53.625 --> 51:54.917
- After all
we ve been through.

51:54.917 --> 51:57.125
- No, it s correct.
It says Jackson Hole.

51:57.125 --> 51:58.875
- What more do you want from me?

51:58.875 --> 52:00.041
- Wasn t that the agreement?

52:00.041 --> 52:02.166
- Yes, until I saw these.

52:09.834 --> 52:11.542
- Oh.

52:11.542 --> 52:14.208
- Ah, a dating website.

52:14.208 --> 52:16.917
Really?
On the hunt already?

52:16.917 --> 52:20.709
- You re the one who wanted
a divorce in the first place.

52:20.709 --> 52:23.333
I m just trying
to move my life forward.

52:23.333 --> 52:25.250
- You are wearing the blue shirt

52:25.250 --> 52:27.542
that I gave you
for your birthday.

52:27.542 --> 52:31.417
- Yeah.
It s a great shirt.

52:31.417 --> 52:34.417
- I always said blue
was your best color.

52:34.417 --> 52:37.792
You do listen to me.

52:37.792 --> 52:40.750
- Of course I do, baby.

52:46.083 --> 52:48.125
You re the most important
person in my life.

52:48.125 --> 52:51.417
- I can t believe you were gonna
give up Jackson Hole.

52:51.417 --> 52:53.542
- I would do anything for you.
You know that.

52:53.542 --> 52:56.417
- Oh, you re so good to me.
I appreciate it.

52:56.417 --> 53:00.125
- So do you want me
to call off the divorce or...

53:00.125 --> 53:01.583
- Call it off.

53:01.583 --> 53:02.750
We are in love.

53:02.750 --> 53:05.375
- We are so in love, baby.

53:09.458 --> 53:11.959
- Well, if you just give me
some more time to explain

53:11.959 --> 53:14.500
or maybe if you
send somebody down here

53:14.500 --> 53:15.709
to meet with our patients?

53:15.709 --> 53:17.000
- I m afraid not, Dr. Curry.

53:17.000 --> 53:18.792
- That s fine.

53:18.792 --> 53:19.959
I understand.

53:19.959 --> 53:21.250
- Take care.

53:21.250 --> 53:23.834
- Thanks for your time.
- Of course.

53:26.834 --> 53:28.959
♪ ♪

53:28.959 --> 53:31.959
- That was the last
foundation, huh?

53:31.959 --> 53:33.208
- Yeah.

53:33.208 --> 53:34.959
They all said the same thing.

53:34.959 --> 53:38.667
We either don t qualify,
or we ve missed deadlines.

53:38.667 --> 53:42.083
- So there s no chance
for a grant this year?

53:42.083 --> 53:44.458
- No.

53:44.458 --> 53:46.625
And without
any more money coming in,

53:46.625 --> 53:48.208
we ll probably only be able
to stay open

53:48.208 --> 53:49.875
until the end of the month.

53:49.875 --> 53:52.667
- And we re already pretty far
into this month.

53:52.667 --> 53:54.291
- We re gonna have to start
telling people.

53:54.291 --> 53:57.750
Would you please pull
a contact list

53:57.750 --> 54:00.000
of all of our patients
and clients?

54:00.000 --> 54:03.041
- Sure.
- Thanks, Andre.

54:03.041 --> 54:05.208
- Yeah.

54:13.333 --> 54:15.250
- Jason?
- Please.

54:18.875 --> 54:21.166
- I take it you heard
about the Ballentines.

54:21.166 --> 54:23.542
- I heard they ended up
calling off the divorce.

54:23.542 --> 54:25.083
- And they terminated
our services.

54:25.083 --> 54:29.166
- Well, because
they don t need us.

54:29.166 --> 54:30.917
I mean, it s not like
we did anything wrong.

54:30.917 --> 54:32.583
- Did you talk
to Mrs. Ballentine

54:32.583 --> 54:33.875
about her personal feelings?

54:33.875 --> 54:36.875
- I offered some advice.

54:36.875 --> 54:39.959
- I will assign you to some
of our low-profile cases.

54:39.959 --> 54:41.542
- Sir, if you ll just
let me explain--

54:41.542 --> 54:42.959
- Kelsey, I admire
your ambition.

54:42.959 --> 54:44.792
I have for the last
couple years.

54:44.792 --> 54:46.959
And you ve been doing great
right where you are.

54:46.959 --> 54:48.917
Maybe that s where you should be
for the time being.

54:48.917 --> 54:50.291
You re still very young.

54:50.291 --> 54:52.041
You will have plenty of
opportunities in your future,

54:52.041 --> 54:54.125
but for now, we ll have to table
our partnership discussion.

54:54.125 --> 54:56.208
- I was just trying to help.

54:56.208 --> 54:59.125
- Kelsey, we re mediators,
not marriage counselors.

54:59.125 --> 55:01.208
Mitch will assign you new cases,

55:01.208 --> 55:03.542
and Mrs. Ballentine
will get in touch with you.

55:03.542 --> 55:05.458
- Why?
- About the dog.

55:05.458 --> 55:07.959
She d like her back.

55:07.959 --> 55:08.875
Now excuse me.

55:13.542 --> 55:16.542
- Well, at least
you ll be rid of the dog.

55:16.542 --> 55:17.583
That s good, right?

55:17.583 --> 55:19.542
- Yeah.

55:19.542 --> 55:26.417
♪ ♪

55:38.041 --> 55:41.500
Harrison, what are you
doing here?

55:41.500 --> 55:44.709
- I, uh--I need
to tell you something,

55:44.709 --> 55:46.542
and I wanted to do it
in person.

55:46.542 --> 55:47.917
- What is it?

55:47.917 --> 55:49.667
- The shelter s
lost its funding.

55:49.667 --> 55:51.250
We lost our grant,

55:51.250 --> 55:53.750
and we re gonna need to close
it down by the end of the month.

55:53.750 --> 55:55.583
- That s horrible.

55:55.583 --> 56:00.250
I m--I m so sorry.

56:00.250 --> 56:03.834
What about all of your clients,
everyone s pets?

56:03.834 --> 56:05.041
- Well, they re gonna
have to find

56:05.041 --> 56:06.667
another animal clinic to use.

56:06.667 --> 56:09.166
- Everybody loves you.

56:09.166 --> 56:10.709
And what about
the therapy program?

56:10.709 --> 56:12.625
- Well, no, that s
at least some good news.

56:12.625 --> 56:15.792
I, uh--I have a friend
from school

56:15.792 --> 56:17.166
who knows about my work,

56:17.166 --> 56:20.583
and, uh, he actually
wants me to come

56:20.583 --> 56:22.625
and start up a program
at his hospital.

56:22.625 --> 56:24.166
- Well, that s great.

56:24.166 --> 56:27.041
So then maybe you don t have
to completely shut down.

56:27.041 --> 56:30.500
Your patients can still
visit you at your new place.

56:30.500 --> 56:31.792
- It s in New York.

56:31.792 --> 56:33.250
- What?

56:33.250 --> 56:34.625
- I would have to move
to New York

56:34.625 --> 56:36.083
in order to start
the program.

56:36.083 --> 56:39.291
- So you re leaving?

56:39.291 --> 56:41.333
Just like that?

56:41.333 --> 56:44.041
- Well, my program
helps people,

56:44.041 --> 56:46.834
and, you know,
I could do good elsewhere

56:46.834 --> 56:48.625
by bringing it
to another city.

56:48.625 --> 56:51.125
- But everybody needs you.

56:51.125 --> 56:53.959
They need their hometown hero.

56:53.959 --> 56:58.458
- Yeah, but without any funding,
I can t help anybody.

56:58.458 --> 57:03.125
- So... there s nothing
keeping you here, then?

57:03.125 --> 57:04.166
- I don t know what you mean.

57:09.041 --> 57:10.625
- What s wrong?

57:10.625 --> 57:11.834
Is everything okay?

57:11.834 --> 57:13.166
- Yeah, I m fine.

57:13.166 --> 57:17.291
I just had a really bad day
at work.

57:17.291 --> 57:18.834
- Well, do you want
to talk about it?

57:18.834 --> 57:21.542
- Oh, no, um--no, no, no,
don t worry about me.

57:21.542 --> 57:27.208
You, um--you ve got your own
problems to figure out.

57:27.208 --> 57:29.667
Take care, Harrison.

57:29.667 --> 57:30.750
- Kelsey, I--

57:40.542 --> 57:42.041
- Hey, is everything okay?

57:42.041 --> 57:43.375
- Uh, yeah, I m fine.

57:43.375 --> 57:46.709
I just, uh, need
to take Daisy for a walk,

57:46.709 --> 57:48.166
clear my head.

57:53.250 --> 57:57.333
- ♪ It s the little things ♪

57:57.333 --> 57:59.417
♪ You left behind ♪

57:59.417 --> 58:02.041
- Okay, Daisy,
you get to run around.

58:02.041 --> 58:04.667
- ♪ I can t forget about ♪

58:04.667 --> 58:07.792
- No, I m not in the mood
to run you around.

58:07.792 --> 58:10.041
I ve had a hard day.

58:10.041 --> 58:11.667
So you ll just have
to do it yourself.

58:13.291 --> 58:16.291
Hey, girl, what s this about?

58:18.041 --> 58:20.333
You re not that bad,
you know that?

58:20.333 --> 58:24.625
If only you would listen to me,
though, like when I say "sit."

58:27.291 --> 58:29.583
Or "down"?

58:31.959 --> 58:33.667
Good girl.

58:36.917 --> 58:39.375
So now you finally
connect with me, huh?

58:42.542 --> 58:43.959
I hate to break it to you,

58:43.959 --> 58:48.917
but this isn t gonna be
for much longer.

58:51.250 --> 58:55.792
Yeah, we both just need
to be strong.

59:06.291 --> 59:12.709
♪ ♪

59:19.959 --> 59:21.667
Oh, man.

59:21.667 --> 59:23.709
- Hey, Kelsey.

59:23.709 --> 59:26.625
- Andre, I m so sorry
about this.

59:28.333 --> 59:32.542
Thanks, but, uh,
I ll get by just fine.

59:32.542 --> 59:35.250
It s the animals and the clients
I m worried about.

59:35.250 --> 59:38.083
We ve had to close so quickly
that almost everybody

59:38.083 --> 59:40.500
had to hear about the situation
through email.

59:40.500 --> 59:43.000
I bet somebody won t even
realize what happened

59:43.000 --> 59:47.083
until they get here
and see the place boarded up.

59:47.083 --> 59:49.000
- Every neighborhood
needs a vet.

59:49.000 --> 59:51.500
- Yeah.

59:51.500 --> 59:53.875
So what are we doing?

59:53.875 --> 59:58.041
- Actually,
we came to say good-bye.

59:58.041 --> 01:00:00.208
I have to give Daisy back soon.

01:00:00.208 --> 01:00:01.500
- Aw!

01:00:01.500 --> 01:00:02.834
Daisy!

01:00:02.834 --> 01:00:04.542
Hey.

01:00:04.542 --> 01:00:05.709
Yeah.

01:00:05.709 --> 01:00:08.083
Ah, gonna miss you, girl.

01:00:11.208 --> 01:00:12.875
She s a good one.

01:00:12.875 --> 01:00:14.792
- I know.

01:00:14.792 --> 01:00:18.125
- Hey, we have some
unopened treats and toys

01:00:18.125 --> 01:00:20.959
in the back
that we can t use anymore.

01:00:20.959 --> 01:00:22.291
Would you want them?

01:00:22.291 --> 01:00:23.291
- Uh, sure.

01:00:23.291 --> 01:00:25.125
Maybe Mrs. Ballentine
could use them.

01:00:25.125 --> 01:00:26.583
That d be great.

01:00:26.583 --> 01:00:28.000
- Okay.

01:00:41.208 --> 01:00:44.709
- Hi, Mrs. Ballentine.

01:00:44.709 --> 01:00:46.750
I thought I would give you
an update

01:00:46.750 --> 01:00:48.750
in case you were wondering
about Daisy.

01:00:51.291 --> 01:00:52.834
She s a good girl,

01:00:52.834 --> 01:00:56.917
really a lot smarter
than she lets on.

01:00:56.917 --> 01:00:59.417
I guess the trick is,

01:00:59.417 --> 01:01:01.583
you need to open up first

01:01:01.583 --> 01:01:04.041
before she feels comfortable
doing the same.

01:01:05.750 --> 01:01:11.417
Um, she s very well-behaved.

01:01:11.417 --> 01:01:14.750
She sits.

01:01:14.750 --> 01:01:18.750
She lies down.

01:01:18.750 --> 01:01:20.166
She doesn t jump on things

01:01:20.166 --> 01:01:23.667
if you don t want her to
anymore.

01:01:23.667 --> 01:01:28.750
It took a little time,
but she gets you.

01:01:31.583 --> 01:01:33.083
See?

01:01:33.083 --> 01:01:36.959
She doesn t even like the crying

01:01:36.959 --> 01:01:40.792
or, apparently,
too much time off-camera.

01:01:43.709 --> 01:01:45.875
So, uh, that s it
for this update,

01:01:45.875 --> 01:01:49.417
um, last one, I guess.

01:01:49.417 --> 01:01:51.458
I ll see you soon.

01:01:53.542 --> 01:01:54.959
- Ah.

01:01:57.959 --> 01:02:00.750
With everything
that s happening,

01:02:00.750 --> 01:02:02.291
I ve had tears too.

01:02:02.291 --> 01:02:05.500
- It s just so awful
that this place has to go.

01:02:11.041 --> 01:02:16.166
I mean, you guys have done
so much for so many people.

01:02:16.166 --> 01:02:19.834
- Yeah, it s too bad there isn t
somebody to do something for us.

01:02:19.834 --> 01:02:21.458
- Do you have
a contact list handy

01:02:21.458 --> 01:02:22.709
of all the clients
you ve helped?

01:02:22.709 --> 01:02:24.500
- Yeah, of course.

01:02:24.500 --> 01:02:27.875
We might be a small operation,
but we re still efficient.

01:02:27.875 --> 01:02:30.041
I just need to find--

01:02:30.041 --> 01:02:34.625
Wait, wait, wait.
What do you need a copy for?

01:02:34.625 --> 01:02:37.750
- I have an idea.

01:02:41.667 --> 01:02:43.917
- Okay, Smith family
with two golden retrievers

01:02:43.917 --> 01:02:45.333
does not answer their phone.

01:02:45.333 --> 01:02:46.834
- You left a message, right?
- Yeah.

01:02:46.834 --> 01:02:49.125
- Send an email?
- Okay.

01:02:51.792 --> 01:02:53.375
- Stacee.

01:02:53.375 --> 01:02:55.500
- All right,
what s the emergency?

01:02:55.500 --> 01:02:59.291
- I need your fund-raising
skills for a very good cause.

01:02:59.291 --> 01:03:03.542
Here, call these people.

01:03:03.542 --> 01:03:06.208
- Okay.

01:03:06.208 --> 01:03:07.875
How long is this gonna take?

01:03:07.875 --> 01:03:09.583
- It could take all night,

01:03:09.583 --> 01:03:12.000
but I will provide
the pizza and the wine.

01:03:12.000 --> 01:03:13.417
- All the motivation I need.

01:03:13.417 --> 01:03:15.542
Let s get to work.

01:03:15.542 --> 01:03:21.709
♪ ♪

01:03:21.709 --> 01:03:24.083
This is the contact list
from the vet s office.

01:03:24.083 --> 01:03:26.375
- Yes, it is.

01:03:26.375 --> 01:03:27.583
- Okay.

01:03:31.500 --> 01:03:33.542
It s for a great cause.

01:03:33.542 --> 01:03:35.875
This program has helped so many
people in the community.

01:03:35.875 --> 01:03:37.250
- I d be happy to donate.

01:03:37.250 --> 01:03:39.583
- Oh, thank you so much.
- You re welcome.

01:03:39.583 --> 01:03:42.083
- Don t worry about the amount.
Any little bit helps.

01:03:42.083 --> 01:03:44.000
- Perfect. I ll take care
of it right away.

01:03:47.792 --> 01:03:50.250
- Ms. Peterson is in
for $250.

01:03:50.250 --> 01:03:52.625
- Great.
- So where does that put us?

01:03:52.625 --> 01:03:53.458
- Uh...

01:03:55.750 --> 01:03:57.583
Still not enough. Hmm.

01:03:57.583 --> 01:03:59.959
- But we ve called
almost everybody.

01:03:59.959 --> 01:04:02.417
- I guess we have to figure out
a way to go bigger,

01:04:02.417 --> 01:04:03.500
reach more people.

01:04:04.959 --> 01:04:06.083
- I think I got it.

01:04:06.083 --> 01:04:07.917
- What do you need me to do?

01:04:07.917 --> 01:04:09.333
- Get more wine and pizza.

01:04:09.333 --> 01:04:12.083
- On it.

01:04:12.083 --> 01:04:13.917
- Everybody knows there have
been a lot of changes

01:04:13.917 --> 01:04:16.041
in this practice
in the last few days.

01:04:16.041 --> 01:04:17.959
But that only means
that we have to work harder

01:04:17.959 --> 01:04:20.834
and do what we can
to bring in more business.

01:04:20.834 --> 01:04:22.375
- Our client lists
are bloated as is.

01:04:22.375 --> 01:04:24.667
We need to come up with a way
to even out the workflow.

01:04:24.667 --> 01:04:25.667
- Nonsense.

01:04:25.667 --> 01:04:27.542
We don t change a thing.

01:04:27.542 --> 01:04:29.875
This firm is moving
in the right direction.

01:04:29.875 --> 01:04:31.875
- I guess backwards
is definitely a direction.

01:04:31.875 --> 01:04:33.333
- We got to keep pushing.

01:04:33.333 --> 01:04:40.000
♪ ♪

01:04:43.625 --> 01:04:44.959
You know what these are?

01:04:44.959 --> 01:04:46.458
- More potential clients?

01:04:46.458 --> 01:04:47.667
- That s right.

01:04:47.667 --> 01:04:48.667
- All of those?

01:04:48.667 --> 01:04:50.709
- These are a partnership

01:04:50.709 --> 01:04:52.291
that is no longer,

01:04:52.291 --> 01:04:54.333
but these people need us,

01:04:54.333 --> 01:04:56.500
even though
they might not know it,

01:04:56.500 --> 01:04:57.959
because they can t decide
on their own.

01:04:57.959 --> 01:04:59.834
They re separated,
they re disconnected,

01:04:59.834 --> 01:05:02.208
and they have no type
of support.

01:05:02.208 --> 01:05:03.834
And that s where we step in,

01:05:03.834 --> 01:05:07.166
because we have to finalize
all these divorces,

01:05:07.166 --> 01:05:09.041
which means we have to work
longer hours

01:05:09.041 --> 01:05:11.166
and nights and weekends.

01:05:11.166 --> 01:05:13.542
We have to do that
for the future of this firm.

01:05:22.250 --> 01:05:23.709
What s going on, Mitch?

01:05:23.709 --> 01:05:25.000
- Yeah, I think I need to leave.

01:05:25.000 --> 01:05:27.500
- But we re in a meeting.

01:05:27.500 --> 01:05:28.917
Mitch!

01:05:33.834 --> 01:05:40.750
♪ ♪

01:05:50.709 --> 01:05:51.917
- Doing okay?

01:05:51.917 --> 01:05:53.750
- Yeah.

01:05:53.750 --> 01:05:56.709
Got plenty of file boxes,
and I actually think

01:05:56.709 --> 01:05:59.208
most of this stuff
can just be thrown out.

01:05:59.208 --> 01:06:01.792
- No, man, that--
that s not what I mean.

01:06:01.792 --> 01:06:05.542
Are you doing okay?

01:06:05.542 --> 01:06:07.125
- Of course.

01:06:08.333 --> 01:06:12.875
Got the new job lined up
and everything, so...

01:06:12.875 --> 01:06:17.542
- You know, um, Kelsey
came here the other day.

01:06:17.542 --> 01:06:19.041
- I know.

01:06:19.041 --> 01:06:20.458
- You didn t come out
of your office.

01:06:20.458 --> 01:06:21.959
- I know.

01:06:21.959 --> 01:06:24.500
- Well, didn t you want
to talk to her,

01:06:24.500 --> 01:06:27.375
tell her about everything,
say good-bye at least?

01:06:29.917 --> 01:06:33.542
- I said good-bye.

01:06:33.542 --> 01:06:37.917
I tried to talk, but I didn t
want to bother her.

01:06:37.917 --> 01:06:40.083
She was upset about work
or something.

01:06:40.083 --> 01:06:41.875
- I think you know
why she was upset.

01:06:46.208 --> 01:06:48.750
She likes you, Harrison,

01:06:48.750 --> 01:06:50.417
and you like her too.

01:06:50.417 --> 01:06:52.083
It s obvious.

01:06:57.750 --> 01:07:01.375
You re right.

01:07:01.375 --> 01:07:02.750
Do you think she knows
how I feel?

01:07:02.750 --> 01:07:05.500
- Of course not.

01:07:05.500 --> 01:07:08.000
Look, you have a problem with
that kind of thing, Harrison,

01:07:08.000 --> 01:07:10.125
connecting with people,

01:07:10.125 --> 01:07:12.000
and usually when someone
has a problem,

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:15.959
it s easier for them to work
around it than to fix it.

01:07:15.959 --> 01:07:18.333
That s why you work with animals
and not with people.

01:07:18.333 --> 01:07:20.750
But some problems,
you just can t ignore.

01:07:20.750 --> 01:07:22.333
You have to work on them.

01:07:22.333 --> 01:07:23.375
You have to grow.

01:07:23.375 --> 01:07:25.792
You have to change.

01:07:29.875 --> 01:07:31.667
- That s what you came in here
to say, isn t it?

01:07:31.667 --> 01:07:33.041
- Of course.

01:07:33.041 --> 01:07:35.250
I practiced the whole speech
multiple times and everything.

01:07:35.250 --> 01:07:36.917
Did it come off sincere?

01:07:36.917 --> 01:07:38.792
I wanted it to be sincere
but not mean.

01:07:38.792 --> 01:07:40.333
- No, it was good.

01:07:40.333 --> 01:07:43.000
It was good.

01:07:43.000 --> 01:07:45.041
Could have just opened
with it, though,

01:07:45.041 --> 01:07:46.125
gotten straight to the point.

01:07:46.125 --> 01:07:47.250
You know I prefer that.

01:07:47.250 --> 01:07:49.083
- I know. I know. I know.

01:08:01.291 --> 01:08:02.500
- Are you gonna be okay?

01:08:02.500 --> 01:08:04.000
- Me? Totally.

01:08:04.000 --> 01:08:06.959
I got three jobs lined up
at other clinics already, so...

01:08:06.959 --> 01:08:08.500
- Really?
- Yeah.

01:08:08.500 --> 01:08:10.667
Having the hometown hero
as your boss

01:08:10.667 --> 01:08:12.125
really bolsters your résumé.

01:08:13.667 --> 01:08:18.041
♪ ♪

01:08:29.542 --> 01:08:36.417
♪ ♪

01:08:58.041 --> 01:08:59.917
- Mitch?

01:08:59.917 --> 01:09:01.542
- Back here.

01:09:06.875 --> 01:09:09.625
- What is all this?

01:09:09.625 --> 01:09:11.250
You put the crib together.

01:09:11.250 --> 01:09:12.457
- Can t you tell?

01:09:12.457 --> 01:09:14.000
It s a nursery.

01:09:14.000 --> 01:09:15.917
I, uh--I chose green
cause it seemed like a--

01:09:15.917 --> 01:09:17.166
a good neutral color.

01:09:17.166 --> 01:09:18.625
I didn t want to do
pink or blue

01:09:18.625 --> 01:09:20.457
because we don t know
if it s a boy or a girl yet.

01:09:20.457 --> 01:09:22.834
But I know, I know--you don t
buy into gender stereotypes,

01:09:22.834 --> 01:09:25.500
so even if we did know,
you probably would have--

01:09:25.500 --> 01:09:26.875
you probably would have
wanted to paint it

01:09:26.875 --> 01:09:28.917
a different color anyway.

01:09:28.917 --> 01:09:30.041
What is it?
- Uh...

01:09:30.041 --> 01:09:31.625
- It s the crib, huh?

01:09:31.625 --> 01:09:33.207
I know, it looks--
it looks big,

01:09:33.207 --> 01:09:35.250
but babies on my side
of the family,

01:09:35.250 --> 01:09:36.500
they tend to run
on the large side,

01:09:36.500 --> 01:09:38.375
which I realize
is definitely something

01:09:38.375 --> 01:09:39.625
you should have
known about before now.

01:09:39.625 --> 01:09:41.166
- No, I love it.

01:09:41.166 --> 01:09:44.875
I-I love all of it.

01:09:44.875 --> 01:09:47.375
What are you even doing here?

01:09:47.375 --> 01:09:48.457
- I m here for this.

01:09:49.917 --> 01:09:52.792
I realized something at work.

01:09:52.792 --> 01:09:55.583
The way Jason was discussing
what happens in bad marriages,

01:09:55.583 --> 01:09:59.291
it made it clear to me
that I love what we have.

01:09:59.291 --> 01:10:04.000
I love you and our future family
more than anything else,

01:10:04.000 --> 01:10:07.041
so I got up, and I walked out.

01:10:07.041 --> 01:10:09.375
- You just walked out?
- Yeah.

01:10:09.375 --> 01:10:11.041
- What if you lose your job?

01:10:11.041 --> 01:10:15.125
- Just as long
as I don t lose you.

01:10:15.125 --> 01:10:17.625
Both of you.

01:10:17.625 --> 01:10:19.083
- We re not going anywhere.

01:10:25.667 --> 01:10:31.166
♪ ♪

01:10:35.583 --> 01:10:37.125
- Hello.

01:10:37.125 --> 01:10:38.709
- Mrs. Ballentine.

01:10:38.709 --> 01:10:40.250
- Oh, you act like
you weren t expecting me.

01:10:40.250 --> 01:10:41.542
- No, I-I was.

01:10:41.542 --> 01:10:44.917
I just, uh, lost track of time,

01:10:44.917 --> 01:10:47.542
but I have all of Daisy s things
ready for you.

01:10:47.542 --> 01:10:49.834
- Good, I was hoping it would be
a quick in and out.

01:10:49.834 --> 01:10:52.458
Thomas is waiting for us
at home.

01:10:54.500 --> 01:10:56.625
You know, I owe you so much
thanks and gratitude

01:10:56.625 --> 01:10:58.500
for the advice you gave me.

01:10:58.500 --> 01:11:00.875
Without you, my husband and I
wouldn t be working

01:11:00.875 --> 01:11:03.959
on our marriage,
so thank you so much.

01:11:06.166 --> 01:11:08.000
If there s anything
that I can do--

01:11:08.000 --> 01:11:09.333
- Oh, don t worry about it.

01:11:09.333 --> 01:11:12.834
I m just glad that you
worked things out.

01:11:12.834 --> 01:11:15.500
You know, when you have
a connection

01:11:15.500 --> 01:11:17.709
with someone
that you truly love...

01:11:21.959 --> 01:11:24.625
You shouldn t let them
get away.

01:11:24.625 --> 01:11:27.542
- Well, thanks again--
and for watching Daisy.

01:11:28.750 --> 01:11:30.792
Come on, Daisy.

01:11:30.792 --> 01:11:32.041
- Oh, don t forget this.

01:11:32.041 --> 01:11:33.792
- Ah, thank you.

01:11:33.792 --> 01:11:34.917
Take care.

01:11:43.583 --> 01:11:44.875
Oh!

01:11:47.583 --> 01:11:53.875
♪ ♪

01:11:55.583 --> 01:11:57.917
- Jason would like to see you
in the conference room.

01:11:57.917 --> 01:12:01.417
- Oh, um, I ll be there
in just a sec.

01:12:06.041 --> 01:12:07.166
You wanted to see me?

01:12:07.166 --> 01:12:08.417
Mitch?

01:12:08.417 --> 01:12:09.417
- Please.

01:12:09.417 --> 01:12:10.667
- I thought that you were--

01:12:10.667 --> 01:12:12.166
- Crazy...

01:12:12.166 --> 01:12:14.083
after having a breakdown
and storming out?

01:12:14.083 --> 01:12:16.000
- I was gonna say on leave.

01:12:16.000 --> 01:12:18.208
- Mitch came back here to talk,

01:12:18.208 --> 01:12:23.375
and after he apologized,
we had a civilized discussion.

01:12:23.375 --> 01:12:25.750
Let me start this discussion
with an apology to you.

01:12:25.750 --> 01:12:27.333
Mitch and I talked
about how, recently,

01:12:27.333 --> 01:12:30.750
the workflow hasn t been
well-managed.

01:12:30.750 --> 01:12:32.667
It made me realize that
taking on lots of accounts

